-- 944
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'944', N'944', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Founded in Phoenix, expanded to a nationwide presence, this once thriving lifestyle publication navigated both great success and bankruptcy before its closure in 2011.}}*944* was a regional fashion, entertainment, and lifestyle publication that operated in the United States from 2001 to 2011. This noteworthy publication was the brainchild of the original *944 Media* company, founded by Marc Lotenberg in Phoenix, Arizona, in 2001. With time, it became part of *944 Media* based in Los Angeles, marking a significant phase in its evolution.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In a bold move that showcased the magazine’s growth and expanding influence, *944 Media* announced the acquisition of *Six Degrees* in March 2009. *Six Degrees* was a competing upscale lifestyle magazine with editions in Atlanta, Detroit, Miami, and Las Vegas, as well as an accompanying web portal. By October of that year, *944 Media* ceased the publication of *Six Degrees* and launched two new editions of *944* to penetrate the Atlanta and Detroit markets. The magazine’s expansion continued in April 2010 with the launch of its tenth edition, this time targeting the Dallas market.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'However, despite its expansion and success, the company faced significant challenges. In April 2010, *944 Media, LLC.* declared Chapter 11 bankruptcy in the United States Bankruptcy Court for the Central District of California, Los Angeles Division. The company was represented by Landau Gottfried & Berger LLP during this period.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ultimately, on June 1, 2011, *944* announced the publication of their last issue and the permanent closure of the business. This marked the end of a decade-long journey that had seen the magazine grow from a local Phoenix publication to a nationwide lifestyle brand.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- British Chess Magazine
--INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
--VALUES ( N'British Chess Magazine', N'british-chess-magazine', 1, 'en' );
--INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
--VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A British magazine providing chess enthusiasts worldwide with news, analysis, and commentary, featuring games from top-level tournaments and historical matches.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'**British Chess Magazine**, also known as *BCM*, is a monthly English-language magazine devoted to the game of chess. Established in 1881, it is one of the world''s oldest chess magazines still in existence. The magazine is primarily focused on coverage of major chess events, instructive analysis of games, chess history, and other chess-related subjects.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was initially edited by John Watkinson from 1881 until his death in 1906. Under his leadership, *British Chess Magazine* gained prominence for its detailed analysis and comprehensive coverage of chess games, events, and news. The magazine''s early issues also included problems, reviews, and biographical sketches of eminent chess players.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'During the twentieth century, *BCM* continued to evolve, covering the significant developments in chess and fostering the growth of the chess community in the United Kingdom and worldwide. In the digital age, the magazine maintains an online presence, complementing its print issues with an interactive website and social media platforms.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*British Chess Magazine* has been instrumental in documenting the evolution of chess through its in-depth articles, interviews, reviews, and commentaries. The magazine''s longevity and sustained quality have established it as a respected voice in the world of chess, cherished by amateurs and professionals alike.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite the immense transformation of the media landscape since its founding, *BCM* remains committed to its original mission: promoting chess through comprehensive coverage, insightful analysis, and fostering a global community of chess enthusiasts. Its rich history and continued relevance make *British Chess Magazine* a significant institution in the chess world.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Bound & Gagged
--INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
--VALUES ( N'Bound & Gagged', N'bound-and-gagged', 1, 'en' );
--INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
--VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A pioneering BDSM magazine featuring articles and advice on safe and consensual sexual practices, interviews with experts and enthusiasts, and more.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*Bound & Gagged* was a niche publication that emerged in the latter half of the 20th century, catering to a specific subset of the gay male community with an interest in bondage and discipline, dominance and submission, and sadomasochism, collectively known as BDSM. The magazine was launched in 1987 and continued its publication until 2005.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*Bound & Gagged* distinguished itself through its focus on the exploration and celebration of consensual kink and fetish practices within the gay male community. It was a publication that sought to create a space for discourse and representation of a subculture that, at the time, was often marginalized and misunderstood.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The content of *Bound & Gagged* was an amalgamation of various elements, including fictional stories, personal accounts, interviews with prominent figures in the BDSM community, and practical guides on safe and consensual kink practices. The magazine’s prose was characterized by candor and frankness, reflective of its commitment to authenticity.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its textual content, *Bound & Gagged* featured visual imagery and photographs that depicted various aspects of BDSM culture. These visuals, though explicit in nature, were presented with an emphasis on aesthetic sensibilities, and sought to convey the diversity and depth of experiences within the community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the defining characteristics of *Bound & Gagged* was its commitment to promoting safe, consensual, and informed engagement with BDSM practices. This commitment manifested in the publication’s emphasis on education and the dissemination of information pertaining to safety and consent.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'At a time when the BDSM community was often subject to stigmatization and misconception, *Bound & Gagged* stood as a bastion for the affirmation and empowerment of its readership. Through its pages, it fostered a sense of community and belonging among individuals who found solace and identity in the exploration of alternative sexual expressions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Though *Bound & Gagged* ceased publication in 2005, its impact within the gay male BDSM community remains significant. It is remembered as a pioneering publication that contributed to the visibility and validation of a vibrant subculture, and as an emblem of the ongoing journey toward greater inclusivity and understanding within the broader tapestry of human experience.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Boy's Own Paper
--INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
--VALUES ( N'The Boy''s Own Paper', N'the-boys-own-paper', 1, 'en' );
--INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
--VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A British periodical that specialized in adventure and education for boys. It contained fiction, non-fiction, and practical articles on various subjects.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Boy''s Own Paper* was a beloved British periodical that commenced its publication in January 1879, capturing the imaginations of young boys across the British Isles and beyond for nearly a century until its final issue in 1967. Through its pages, *The Boy''s Own Paper* instilled virtues of courage, honour, and integrity, while simultaneously igniting a zest for adventure and discovery.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The contents of *The Boy''s Own Paper* were both varied and edifying. The magazine featured a veritable smorgasbord of tales of derring-do, historical narratives, articles on science and nature, and guides to crafting and hobbies. The fiction was particularly enthralling, with stories of gallant heroes embarking on swashbuckling adventures, oftentimes accompanied by illustrations that further enlivened the text.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to fiction, *The Boy''s Own Paper* provided its readers with educational content, thereby striking a delicate balance between entertainment and edification. Articles on science, geography, and history imbued the readers with knowledge, while features on sports and outdoor pursuits encouraged physical activity and a love for the natural world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'A distinctive aspect of *The Boy''s Own Paper* was its emphasis on moral and character development. The magazine sought to mould young minds into upstanding gentlemen, espousing values such as honesty, bravery, and perseverance. These themes were recurrent throughout the stories and articles, often delivered through protagonists who embodied these traits.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Moreover, *The Boy''s Own Paper* served as a platform for the readers to engage with the magazine and with each other. The periodical encouraged its audience to submit stories, poems, and illustrations, and included a section for readers'' letters. This interaction fostered a sense of community among the young readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The aesthetic of *The Boy''s Own Paper* was characteristic of the era, with an emphasis on intricate illustrations and ornate typography. The magazine''s covers often depicted scenes of adventure and excitement, enticing the readers to delve into the stories within.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In the annals of literary history, *The Boy''s Own Paper* occupies a hallowed space. It was not merely a magazine, but rather a companion and guide for countless young boys as they navigated the formative years of their lives. Through the chronicles of heroes, the wonders of science, and the virtues of character, *The Boy''s Own Paper* was an invaluable treasure that enriched the hearts and minds of its readers.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

