VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A pioneering magazine that explored the world of CD-ROM technology, providing comprehensive information, reviews, and industry insights.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*CD-ROM Today* was a renowned publication dedicated to the world of compact disc-read only memory (CD-ROM) technology.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Establishment and Focus' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*CD-ROM Today Magazine* was established to cater to the growing interest in CD-ROM technology during the late 1980s and early 1990s. The magazine aimed to provide readers with comprehensive information and reviews regarding CD-ROM software, hardware, and industry trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured a wide range of articles covering various aspects of CD-ROM technology. It provided readers with in-depth reviews of CD-ROM software titles, exploring their features, gameplay, and overall quality. *CD-ROM Today Magazine* also covered hardware advancements, including CD-ROM drives, multimedia kits, and emerging technologies in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Expert Contributors and Analysis' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*CD-ROM Today Magazine* enlisted the expertise of industry professionals, software developers, and technology enthusiasts to provide readers with expert analysis and insights. The magazine aimed to address the technical aspects of CD-ROM technology, discussing topics such as data storage, encoding formats, multimedia integration, and emerging standards.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Software Demos and Exclusives' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine often included CD-ROM demos and exclusive software titles with each issue. These demos allowed readers to experience firsthand the latest advancements in CD-ROM technology, showcasing the potential of interactive multimedia content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Industry Coverage and News' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*CD-ROM Today Magazine* kept readers up to date with the latest news and developments in the CD-ROM industry. It covered topics such as new software releases, industry events, partnerships, and technological advancements. The magazine aimed to provide a comprehensive overview of the rapidly evolving CD-ROM landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Print Format and Transition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Initially published in print format, *CD-ROM Today Magazine* offered readers a tangible publication that they could collect and refer to. However, in the late 1990s, as the internet became more prevalent, the magazine transitioned to an online platform, adapting to the changing media landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'While the specific details of *CD-ROM Today Magazine*''s discontinuation are unavailable, its legacy remains in the collective knowledge and influence it had on the CD-ROM industry and technology enthusiasts. The magazine played a significant role in promoting and educating readers about the potential of CD-ROM technology, helping shape the future of multimedia content delivery.{{Category Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Century Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Century Magazine', N'the-century-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A prominent American publication of the late 19th and early 20th centuries, featuring influential literature, art, history, and commentary.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Century Magazine*, originally known as *Scribner''s Monthly* until 1881, was a prominent American publication that played a significant role in shaping the literary and cultural landscape of the late 19th and early 20th centuries.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Establishment and Focus' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Established in 1870 by Roswell Smith and Josiah Gilbert Holland, *The Century Magazine* aimed to provide readers with a diverse range of content, including literature, art, history, politics, and social issues. The magazine sought to engage and enlighten its audience, becoming one of the leading periodicals of its time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Notable Contributors and Literary Works' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Century Magazine* featured contributions from renowned writers, poets, and intellectuals of the time. Prominent authors such as Mark Twain, Henry James, and Edith Wharton published their works in the magazine, contributing to its reputation as a literary powerhouse. The publication also showcased serialized novels, short stories, and poetry, attracting readers with its high-quality literary content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Historical and Political Commentary' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its literary focus, *The Century Magazine* also delved into historical and political commentary. The magazine published articles and essays that provided insights into significant events and issues of the era, including the American Civil War, Reconstruction, and the Gilded Age. These thought-provoking pieces offered readers a deeper understanding of the societal and political climate of the time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Art and Illustration' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Century Magazine* was known for its commitment to visual arts. The publication featured notable illustrations by renowned artists such as Winslow Homer, Frederic Remington, and Howard Pyle. These illustrations accompanied articles, stories, and poetry, enhancing the reading experience and solidifying the magazine''s reputation as a platform for artistic expression.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Social and Cultural Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With its wide-ranging content and influential contributors, *The Century Magazine* played a crucial role in shaping public opinion and cultural discourse. The publication''s coverage of societal issues, literary achievements, and artistic endeavors contributed to the intellectual and cultural development of the era.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Transition and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1930, *The Century Magazine* merged with *The Forum* to become *The Century and Forum*. This merger allowed the publication to continue its legacy of providing thought-provoking content and fostering intellectual discourse. However, the magazine eventually ceased publication in 1930, marking the end of an era.{{Category Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Chap-Book
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Chap-Book', N'the-chap-book', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An influential American literary magazine of the late 19th century, showcasing avant-garde works by emerging writers and artists.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Chap-Book*, also known as *The Chapbook*, was an influential American literary magazine that emerged in the late 19th century and played a significant role in the development of modern literature and art.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origins and Purpose' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Founded in 1894 by Herbert Stuart Stone, *The Chap-Book* aimed to provide a platform for emerging writers and artists to showcase their work. The magazine sought to challenge traditional literary norms and championed experimental and avant-garde styles, making it a pivotal publication during the transition from the Victorian era to the modernist movement.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Literary Contributions' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Chap-Book* featured works from notable writers and poets, including Oscar Wilde, Willa Cather, and H.G. Wells. The magazine published a mix of poetry, short stories, essays, and book reviews, showcasing a wide range of literary talent and offering readers a diverse reading experience.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Artistic Collaboration' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its literary focus, *The Chap-Book* also emphasized the visual arts. The magazine collaborated with prominent artists and illustrators, such as Aubrey Beardsley and Will Bradley, who contributed striking and innovative illustrations to accompany the written content. These collaborations helped create a unique aesthetic for the magazine and further elevated its status in the artistic community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Influence and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*The Chap-Book* played a crucial role in shaping the literary and artistic landscape of the time. It embraced experimental and non-traditional forms of writing, paving the way for the modernist movement that would dominate the early 20th century. The magazine''s commitment to showcasing emerging talents and pushing the boundaries of artistic expression left a lasting impact on the literary world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Transition and End' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1899, *The Chap-Book* underwent a transformation and merged with another publication called *The Dial*. This merger resulted in the birth of *The Dial*, a highly influential literary and cultural magazine that continued to champion avant-garde and modernist works.{{Category Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

