anded its presence to other platforms such as social media, YouTube, and streaming services. The company adapted its content to suit the preferences of its audience on these platforms, consistently delivering humor and entertainment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Transition and Evolution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2018, *College Humor* underwent a transition and rebranding, focusing more on its YouTube channel and digital video content. The company continued to produce comedic videos and sketches, targeting a broader audience beyond just college students.{{Category Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

