VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription *A pioneering publication in the home computer industry, providing valuable resources and empowering enthusiasts with programming tutorials and software recommendations.*}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*COMPUTE!* was a popular publication in the field of home computer technology, providing valuable information and resources to computer enthusiasts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origins and History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*Compute! Magazine* was first launched in 1979, catering to the growing community of home computer users. It quickly gained traction and became a leading source of information for hobbyists, programmers, and early adopters of personal computers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Focus' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a broad range of topics related to home computing, including hardware reviews, programming tutorials, software recommendations, and tips and tricks for getting the most out of various computer systems. *Compute! Magazine* aimed to empower its readers by providing them with the knowledge and resources needed to explore and utilize their computers effectively.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Notable Sections and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the notable sections of *Compute! Magazine* was "Compute!''s Gazette," which featured type-in programs written by readers and contributed by the magazine''s staff. These programs covered a wide range of applications, from games to utilities, and allowed readers to expand their computer capabilities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Another popular feature was the "Compute! Books" section, which reviewed and recommended books related to computer technology, programming, and software development.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'*Compute! Magazine* played a significant role in shaping the home computer revolution of the 1980s. It provided a platform for enthusiasts to exchange ideas, learn new skills, and stay up-to-date with the latest developments in the rapidly evolving field of personal computing.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s accessible and informative content helped democratize computer technology, making it more approachable for a wider audience. It inspired many readers to explore programming and software development, contributing to the growth of the home computing industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Print and Digital Presence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Originally published as a print magazine, *Compute! Magazine* adapted to the digital age and expanded its online presence. The magazine ceased its print publication in 1994 but continued to provide digital content through its website and online community for several more years.{{Category Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

