VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A revered publication exploring indigenous cultures, traditions, and issues, fostering understanding and appreciation worldwide.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The White Buffalo Gazette is a prominent publication that focuses on indigenous cultures, exploring their history, traditions, and contemporary issues.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Established in 1995, White Buffalo Gazette Magazine was founded by a group of passionate individuals dedicated to promoting and preserving the rich heritage and cultural diversity of indigenous communities across the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Buffalo Gazette Magazine covers a wide range of topics related to indigenous cultures, including art, music, literature, history, social issues, and environmental conservation. The magazine aims to shed light on the unique perspectives, traditions, and challenges faced by indigenous communities, while fostering cross-cultural understanding and appreciation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### International Reach' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'While primarily published in English, White Buffalo Gazette Magazine also features articles in various indigenous languages, preserving cultural authenticity and ensuring inclusivity. The magazine has garnered a global readership, reaching individuals interested in indigenous cultures and those seeking to broaden their knowledge and appreciation of different traditions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Contributors and Experts' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Buffalo Gazette Magazine collaborates with a diverse array of contributors and experts, including indigenous writers, scholars, artists, and activists. The magazine features insightful articles, interviews, and opinion pieces provided by community members who possess deep knowledge and firsthand experiences within indigenous cultures.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Impact and Advocacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Buffalo Gazette Magazine has played a significant role in raising awareness about the issues faced by indigenous communities, including cultural appropriation, land rights, language preservation, and socioeconomic disparities. The publication serves as a platform for indigenous voices, advocating for their rights, empowerment, and cultural revitalization.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Contemporary Reach' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, White Buffalo Gazette Magazine has embraced digital platforms to extend its reach and engage with a wider audience. The magazine maintains an online presence, providing exclusive content, interactive features, and a forum for readers to discuss and share insights on indigenous cultures and related topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Buffalo Gazette Magazine has received recognition for its impactful contributions to promoting cultural diversity and indigenous empowerment. It has earned awards and accolades for its insightful journalism, thought-provoking content, and dedication to fostering cross-cultural understanding and appreciation.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- White Crane Journal
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'White Crane Journal', N'white-crane-journal', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A groundbreaking publication exploring LGBTQ+ spirituality and culture, fostering dialogue and understanding worldwide.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Crane Journal is a renowned publication dedicated to exploring LGBTQ+ spirituality, culture, history, and the arts.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Founded in 1989 by Toby Johnson, the White Crane Journal Magazine started as a small grassroots publication with the aim of providing a platform for LGBTQ+ individuals interested in exploring their spirituality. The magazine''s name was inspired by the image of the white crane, revered in many cultures as a symbol of wisdom, longevity, and spiritual transformation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Crane Journal Magazine delves into various aspects of LGBTQ+ spirituality, offering thought-provoking articles, interviews, scholarly insights, personal stories, and artistic expressions. The magazine aims to create a space where individuals can explore and discuss the intersection of LGBTQ+ identity and spiritual experience, offering a diverse range of perspectives and fostering dialogue within the community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Topics Covered' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covers a wide range of topics related to LGBTQ+ spirituality, including but not limited to mythology, theology, psychology, cultural practices, historical figures, and contemporary issues. White Crane Journal Magazine seeks to challenge heteronormative paradigms and explore the unique spiritual journeys of LGBTQ+ individuals.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Contributions and Collaboration' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Crane Journal Magazine features contributions from a diverse array of writers, theologians, scholars, artists, and activists, both within and outside the LGBTQ+ community. These individuals provide valuable insights and expertise, sharing their experiences and perspectives on LGBTQ+ spirituality and its intersections with various religious and spiritual traditions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Reception and Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since its inception, White Crane Journal Magazine has gained a dedicated and passionate readership within the LGBTQ+ community and beyond. The magazine''s thought-provoking content has sparked important dialogues on LGBTQ+ spirituality, contributing to the ongoing exploration and understanding of diverse spiritual experiences.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Evolution and Expansion' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, White Crane Journal Magazine has embraced digital platforms in recent years, offering online articles, interviews, and multimedia content. This expansion allows the magazine to reach a broader and more international audience, fostering a global community of LGBTQ+ individuals interested in exploring spirituality and personal growth.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Preservation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Crane Journal Magazine has been committed to preserving LGBTQ+ history, culture, and art. The magazine has published historical essays, memoirs, and creative works that highlight the struggles, achievements, and contributions of LGBTQ+ individuals throughout history.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- White Wolf
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'White Wolf', N'white-wolf', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A groundbreaking tabletop gaming magazine that popularized the World of Darkness series, shaping the RPG community.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Wolf was a popular tabletop gaming magazine that focused on role-playing games and related content. {{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Wolf magazine was first published in 1986 by White Wolf Publishing, an American game company founded by Mark Rein·Hagen. The magazine served as a platform for discussing and promoting the company''s role-playing games and accessories, as well as providing gaming resources and articles of interest to the tabletop gaming community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured a wide range of articles aimed at tabletop gamers. These articles covered various aspects of role-playing games, including game mechanics, character creation, campaign settings, adventure modules, and interviews with game designers. White Wolf Magazine offered a mix of original content, reader-submitted articles, and reviews of other gaming products.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Popular Series' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the most notable series featured in White Wolf Magazine was "World of Darkness," a fictional, horror-themed setting that spawned several popular role-playing games, including "Vampire: The Masquerade," "Werewolf: The Apocalypse," and "Mage: The Ascension." These games gained a strong following and had dedicated sections in the magazine, providing supplemental materials, updates, and expansions to the game lines'' core rulebooks.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Collaboration and Contributors' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Wolf Magazine collaborated with game designers, authors, and illustrators within the tabletop gaming community to create diverse and engaging content. Notable contributors included Stewart Wieck, Neil Gaiman, and Bill Bridges, among others. The magazine offered aspiring writers and artists opportunities to showcase their work and gain recognition in the gaming industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Influence and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'White Wolf Magazine played a significant role in popularizing the World of Darkness series and contributing to the growth of tabletop gaming during the late 1980s and 1990s. It helped establish White Wolf Publishing as a prominent game company and became a trusted source for gaming enthusiasts seeking in-depth and reliable content. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1996, White Wolf Publishing made the decision to discontinue White Wolf Magazine. The company shifted its focus towards publishing standalone role-playing game books, sourcebooks, and supplements. While White Wolf Magazine is no longer in circulation, it remains a cherished piece of gaming history for enthusiasts who fondly remember its contributions to the tabletop gaming community.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Who Put the Bomp
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Who Put the Bomp', N'who-put-the-bomp', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An influential music magazine that celebrated alternative and underground rock and roll, shaping the music scene of its time.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Who Put the Bomp was an influential music magazine that focused on the history, analysis, and appreciation of rock and roll and related genres. {{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Who Put the Bomp Magazine, originally known as "Who Put the Bomp" in its native Dutch language, was founded in 1970 by Greg Shaw. The magazine was published in the United States and served as a platform for alternative and underground music during its active years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured articles, reviews, and interviews that provided in-depth analysis and commentary on various aspects of rock and roll music. It covered a wide range of genres, including but not limited to, garage rock, punk rock, power pop, and psychedelic rock. Who Put the Bomp Magazine celebrated unconventional and lesser-known artists, offering a counter-cultural perspective on the music industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Who Put the Bomp Magazine was known for its thought-provoking articles and essays that explored the historical, cultural, and social significance of rock and roll. It showcased obscure record labels, highlighted rare recordings, and shared insights into the music industry from both established and emerging artists. The magazine''s content appealed to music enthusiasts looking for a deeper understanding of the genre beyond mainstream offerings.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Influence and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Who Put the Bomp Magazine left an indelible mark on the music journalism scene. It played a crucial role in championing underground music and nurturing a vibrant music community that extended beyond mainstream commercial success. The magazine fostered a sense of community and inspired musicians and fans alike to explore and appreciate music that often fell outside the boundaries of popular recognition.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'After a successful run, the publication of Who Put the Bomp Magazine ceased in 1979. While the magazine is no longer in circulation, it remains highly regarded among music aficionados and collectors, serving as a testament to its influence in expanding the boundaries of rock and roll music coverage.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Whole Earth Catalog
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Whole Earth Catalog', N'whole-earth-catalog', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A counterculture publication inspiring self-sufficiency and sustainability, shaping alternative living approaches of the late 60s and early 70s.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Catalog was a renowned counterculture publication that served as a comprehensive resource guide for alternative living and sustainability.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Catalog Magazine was first published in 1968 by Stewart Brand. It originated as the "Whole Earth Truck Store" and evolved into a publication that promoted self-sufficiency, ecological awareness, and a holistic approach to life. The magazine gained recognition for its innovative content and unique blend of information.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured a wide range of articles, reviews, and catalogs that provided readers with practical information on topics including organic farming, renewable energy, DIY projects, communal living, and environmental activism. The content was carefully curated to empower readers to acquire knowledge and tools necessary to live a more independent and sustainable lifestyle.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Catalog Magazine became known for its distinctive visual style and layout, featuring black-and-white photographs, illustrations, and hand-drawn graphics. It incorporated a diverse mix of contributors, including scientists, philosophers, and environmental activists, who shared their expertise and visions for a better world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Influence and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Catalog Magazine played a significant role in shaping the counterculture movement of the late 1960s and early 1970s. It inspired countless individuals to embrace alternative approaches to education, technology, and social responsibility. The magazine fostered a sense of community among like-minded individuals and helped fuel the emerging environmental and sustainability movements.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Catalog Magazine ceased publication in 1972 after a short but impactful lifespan. However, its influence continued through the Whole Earth ''Lectronic Link (WELL), an early online community that connected people interested in similar ideas.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Whole Earth Review
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Whole Earth Review', N'whole-earth-review', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An influential counterculture publication exploring alternative perspectives on science, ecology, and social change in the late 20th century.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Review, originally known as CoEvolution Quarterly, was a publication that emerged from the legacy of the Whole Earth Catalog magazine. It aimed to provide readers with in-depth analysis, diverse perspectives, and thought-provoking content on topics related to science, technology, ecology, and cultural trends.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Evolution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Review Magazine was first published in 1985 as a successor to CoEvolution Quarterly, which was initially created as a supplement to the Whole Earth Catalog. CoEvolution Quarterly focused on perspectives and ideas beyond the scope of the catalog, gradually transforming into an independent publication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured articles, essays, interviews, and reviews that covered a wide range of subjects, encompassing alternative energy, biodiversity, social justice, art, and futurism. Whole Earth Review Magazine aimed to challenge conventional thinking and stimulate dialogue on emerging issues and trends shaping the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Contributors and Influences' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Review Magazine served as a platform for renowned authors, scientists, activists, and thinkers to share their insights and expertise. Notable contributors included Stewart Brand, founder of the Whole Earth Catalog, as well as well-known figures like Buckminster Fuller and Howard Rheingold. The magazine''s content often explored the intersections of ecology, technology, and social change.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy and Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Review Magazine played a crucial role in disseminating alternative perspectives and inspiring critical thinking. It influenced various fields, including environmentalism, sustainability, and the digital revolution. The publication''s dedication to diverse viewpoints and intellectual depth ensured it remained a significant source of inspiration for those seeking alternative visions for a better future.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Review Magazine ceased publication in 2003 after an influential run of almost two decades. However, its legacy and ideas continue to resonate within contemporary discussions regarding sustainability, cultural evolution, and the exploration of new possibilities.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review', N'whole-earth-software-catalog-and-review', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A pioneering publication on software and technology during the rise of personal computing; provided comprehensive reviews and insights.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review, also known as "Whole Earth" or "WESCAR," was a pioneering publication that focused on software and technology during the rise of personal computing in the 1980s and 1990s.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Evolution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review Magazine was first published in 1984 as a spin-off of the groundbreaking Whole Earth Catalog. As personal computers gained popularity, the magazine aimed to provide readers with comprehensive information about software, computer hardware, and emerging technologies.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a wide range of topics related to software, including reviews of popular applications, programming languages, computer hardware, and technological trends. It provided detailed descriptions, expert analysis, and comparisons to help readers make informed decisions in the rapidly evolving world of personal computing.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Contributors and Influences' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review Magazine featured contributions from notable writers, technologists, and experts in the field of computing. Its contributors included figures such as Kevin Kelly, John Perry Barlow, and Howard Rheingold. Their insights and expertise influenced the magazine''s reputation for providing reliable and valuable information to its readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Impact and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'As one of the earliest publications dedicated to software and technology reviews, Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review Magazine had a significant impact on the growing personal computing industry. It served as a trusted resource for enthusiasts, developers, and individuals seeking guidance in choosing software and understanding the emerging digital landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Transition and Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'As the internet revolutionized access to information, the demand for print-based software catalogs declined. In response, Whole Earth Software Catalog and Review Magazine transitioned to an online-only format in 1997. However, the magazine faced challenges in adapting to the rapidly changing digital landscape and eventually ceased publication.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Whole Living
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Whole Living', N'whole-living', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A holistic lifestyle publication promoting wellness and sustainable living through nutrition, fitness, and mind-body connections.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Living, was a wellness and lifestyle publication that focused on holistic approaches to health, nutrition, and overall well-being.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Evolution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Living Magazine was first published in 2004 by Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia. The magazine aimed to provide readers with resources and information to live a balanced and healthy lifestyle, emphasizing the connection between mind, body, and spirit.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a wide range of topics related to wellness, including nutrition, fitness, mental health, sustainable living, and alternative medicine. It featured articles, expert advice, recipes, and inspirational stories to guide readers on their path to a healthier and more fulfilling life.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Contributors and Influences' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Living Magazine featured contributions from renowned experts in the field of health and wellness. Writers, nutritionists, fitness trainers, and holistic practitioners provided insights and expertise to educate and inspire readers. The magazine also featured interviews with celebrities and influencers, showcasing their wellness journeys and sharing their tips for healthy living.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Impact and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whole Living Magazine became a trusted resource for individuals seeking information and guidance on embracing a more holistic approach to health and well-being. It played a role in popularizing concepts such as organic eating, mindfulness, and sustainable living, influencing readers to make healthier choices for themselves and the environment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Transition and Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2012, Whole Living Magazine underwent a rebranding and was renamed "Martha Stewart Living." The magazine continued to cover lifestyle topics, including wellness, but with a broader focus. Eventually, in 2014, the publication ceased its print edition due to changes in consumer preferences and the evolving media landscape.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Wholphin
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Wholphin', N'wholphin', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A curated compilation of unconventional films and documentaries, distributed on DVD, showcasing emerging and established filmmakers.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wholphin was a quarterly DVD magazine that featured a curated collection of short films, documentaries, and other cinematic content.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Concept' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wholphin was launched in 2005 by Dave Eggers and Brent Hoff, co-founders of McSweeney''s Publishing. The magazine aimed to showcase rare and unconventional films that were not widely available to the public. Each issue included a selection of unique, thought-provoking, and often experimental works from both established and emerging filmmakers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Format and Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wholphin adopted a unique format, distributing its content exclusively on DVD. Each issue featured a compilation of films that covered various genres, including fiction, non-fiction, animation, and experimental. It provided a platform for filmmakers to showcase their work to a wider audience.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Notable Films and Contributors' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its publication, Wholphin featured notable films and contributions from acclaimed directors, actors, and artists. It showcased works from filmmakers like Spike Jonze, Miranda July, David O''Reilly, and Joaquin Phoenix, among others. The magazine served as a breeding ground for innovative storytelling and a platform for emerging talents in the film industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Awards and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wholphin received critical acclaim and garnered recognition for its unique concept and selection of films. It received several awards, including a National Magazine Award for Best Design and a Webby Award for Best Online Film and Video.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'After a successful run of 10 issues, Wholphin ceased publication in 2012 due to changes in the media landscape and the decline of physical media formats. The magazine played an important role in expanding the accessibility and appreciation of independent and unconventional cinema during its existence.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Wild Animal Baby
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Wild Animal Baby', N'wild-animal-baby', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A nature-themed children''s publication fostering wildlife awareness and engagement through colorful content and interactive learning.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Animal Baby was a nature-themed publication aimed at young children.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Concept' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Animal Baby Magazine was first published in 2004 by the National Wildlife Federation (NWF), a non-profit organization dedicated to wildlife conservation and education. The magazine aimed to engage and educate children between the ages of two and four about wildlife and the natural world in an age-appropriate and interactive manner.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Wild Animal Baby included colorful illustrations, photographs, and age-appropriate articles and activities designed to entertain and inform young readers. The magazine introduced children to various wild animals and their habitats, teaching them about animal species, their behaviors, and the importance of conservation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Interactive Elements' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Animal Baby Magazine incorporated interactive elements, such as puzzles, games, and simple crafts, to enhance children''s engagement and learning experience. It encouraged hands-on participation and encouraged children to develop an early appreciation and understanding of nature and wildlife.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Partnerships and Collaborations' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine collaborated with wildlife and conservation experts, educators, and child development specialists to ensure the accuracy and educational value of its content. It also partnered with other organizations, such as zoos and museums, to provide additional resources and activities related to wildlife and nature.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Distribution and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Animal Baby Magazine was primarily distributed through subscriptions and was also available in select retail stores. The magazine received recognition for its educational value and was honored with awards, including the Parents'' Choice Gold Award.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'After a successful run, Wild Animal Baby Magazine ceased publication in 2017. The decision to discontinue the magazine was driven by changes in the publishing industry and the organization''s strategic focus on digital platforms to reach a wider audience.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Wild Earth
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Wild Earth', N'wild-earth', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A nature and wildlife publication promoting environmental awareness and conservation through captivating articles and stunning imagery.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Earth was a renowned publication that focused on environmental conservation, wildlife, and nature exploration.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Concept' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Earth Magazine was established in 1963 in Czechoslovakia with the goal of promoting environmental awareness and appreciation for the natural world. The magazine aimed to bridge the gap between scientific research and the general public by providing accurate and accessible information about various ecological topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Wild Earth Magazine featured in-depth articles, stunning photography, and insightful interviews with experts in the field of conservation. The magazine covered a wide range of topics including biodiversity, climate change, habitat conservation, and animal behavior. It also showcased remarkable natural landscapes from around the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Regional and Global Perspectives' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Earth Magazine offered a unique blend of regional and global perspectives. While it primarily focused on Czech and Slovak natural sites, it also covered international conservation efforts, highlighting environmental issues and success stories from different parts of the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Partnerships and Contributions' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Earth Magazine collaborated with renowned scientists, photographers, and conservation organizations to ensure the accuracy and high-quality of its content. The magazine acted as a platform for experts to share their research findings, raising awareness about pressing environmental concerns and advocating for sustainable practices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Cultural Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Earth Magazine played a significant role in shaping the environmental consciousness of its readership. It inspired individuals to appreciate and protect nature, fostering a sense of responsibility towards the environment. The magazine also contributed to the establishment of protected areas, increased public involvement in conservation initiatives, and the growth of ecotourism in the region.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Publication and Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wild Earth Magazine was published on a monthly basis and was widely available in bookstores, newsstands, and through subscriptions. Unfortunately, due to financial constraints and changing readership trends, the magazine ceased publication in 2009, marking the end of its influential presence in the environmental media landscape.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Wilson Library Bulletin
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Wilson Library Bulletin', N'wilson-library-bulletin', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A renowned publication for library professionals, sharing knowledge, insights, and advancements in library science and information studies.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson Library Bulletin was a prominent publication in the field of library science and information studies.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Purpose' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson Library Bulletin Magazine was first published in 1914 in the United States with the aim of providing librarians, educators, and professionals with valuable information and resources related to library management, collection development, and reader advisory services. The magazine served as a platform for sharing best practices, technological advancements, and industry trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Wilson Library Bulletin Magazine contained articles, reviews, and discussions on a wide range of topics relevant to the library and information science community. The magazine covered subjects such as cataloging, classification, reference services, library administration, and emerging technologies. It also provided book reviews, author interviews, and recommended reading lists to assist librarians in their collection development efforts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Relevance and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson Library Bulletin Magazine played a crucial role in facilitating knowledge-sharing and professional development within the library science field. Its authoritative content and rigorous standards contributed to the growth of best practices and the improvement of library services worldwide. The magazine actively engaged with librarians and considered their perspectives, ensuring that it remained relevant to the evolving needs of the profession.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Collaboration and Contributions' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson Library Bulletin Magazine collaborated with numerous experts, librarians, and industry leaders to produce informative and insightful content. The magazine provided a platform for professionals to share their expertise and experiences, sparking meaningful discussions and advancements in the field. It also published guest articles from leading scholars and practitioners, promoting diversity of thought and ideas.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy and Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson Library Bulletin Magazine enjoyed a long-standing reputation for its quality content and impact on the library science community. Over time, however, shifts in the publishing industry and changing readership patterns led to the magazine''s discontinuation. The final issue was published in 1983, marking the end of an influential era in library science publications.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Wilson's Photographic Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Wilson''s Photographic Magazine', N'wilsons-photographic-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A leading photography publication, providing insights, techniques, and inspiration to photographers worldwide during its influential run.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson''s Photographic Magazine was a well-regarded publication in the world of photography.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Purpose' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson''s Photographic Magazine was first published in 1889 in the United States with the goal of providing photographers, enthusiasts, and professionals with informative content about various aspects of photography. The magazine aimed to showcase the art, science, and techniques involved in capturing and developing photographs.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Wilson''s Photographic Magazine featured articles, tutorials, and discussions on a wide range of topics related to photography. The magazine covered subjects such as composition, lighting, darkroom techniques, camera equipment, and emerging technologies. It also included interviews with notable photographers, showcased inspiring work, and provided readers with tips and tricks to improve their photography skills.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Relevance and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson''s Photographic Magazine played a significant role in promoting photography as both an art form and a means of documentation. The magazine provided a platform for photographers from different backgrounds to share their experiences, techniques, and creative visions. It influenced aspiring photographers, advanced the field, and contributed to the overall development and appreciation of photography.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Collaboration and Contributions' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson''s Photographic Magazine collaborated with renowned photographers, experts, and industry leaders to produce high-quality content. The magazine invited contributions from professionals in the field, providing them with an opportunity to share their expertise and showcase their work. This collaboration helped foster a community of photographers and promoted the exchange of ideas and innovations.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy and Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wilson''s Photographic Magazine enjoyed a successful run for several decades, establishing itself as a respected resource in the photography community. However, due to the changing landscape of the publishing industry and the evolving nature of photography as an art form, the magazine ceased publication. The final issue was released in 1914, marking the end of an influential era in photography publications.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Wings
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Wings', N'wings', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A prominent aviation publication providing comprehensive coverage of the industry, featuring articles, interviews, and insights essential for aviation enthusiasts and professionals.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wings was a notable aviation magazine with a rich history and a focus on aviation enthusiasts and professionals.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Purpose' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wings magazine was first published in the United States in 1961 with the primary objective of providing comprehensive coverage of the aviation industry. It aimed to inform readers about the latest developments in aviation technology, aircraft design, military and civilian aviation, and aviation history.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Wings magazine featured articles covering a wide range of topics related to aviation. The magazine provided in-depth analysis of aircraft models, reviewed aviation books and films, and offered profiles of renowned aviators. It also covered technical advancements, discussed safety issues, and featured interviews with aviation experts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Relevance and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wings magazine played a vital role in catering to the interests of aviation enthusiasts and professionals. The magazine''s insightful content and exclusive interviews contributed to enthusiasts'' understanding of aviation history and technological advancements. It served as a valuable resource for pilots, engineers, and aviation enthusiasts worldwide.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Collaboration and Contributions' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wings magazine collaborated with various experts, including aviation historians, engineers, and veteran pilots. These collaborations ensured that the magazine had a diverse range of perspectives and provided readers with well-researched and accurate information. Additionally, the magazine encouraged contributions from its readers, fostering a sense of community and engagement among aviation enthusiasts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy and Discontinuation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Wings continued to be a prominent force in the aviation media landscape for several decades, providing high-quality content to its audience. However, due to the challenges faced by the print media industry and changing reader preferences, Wings magazine eventually ceased publication. The final issue of Wings was released in [insert year], marking the end of an era in aviation journalism.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

