VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A progressive publication influential in late 19th-early 20th century. Covered wide range of topics, fostering social reform & stimulating public discourse.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The World''s Work magazine was an influential publication that played a significant role in the late 19th and early 20th centuries.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Origin and Focus' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The World''s Work magazine was first published in 1900 by the publishing company Doubleday, Page & Company, based in the United States. The magazine aimed to provide informative and educational content on a wide range of topics, covering politics, current events, literature, science, and culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured a diverse range of articles, including investigative journalism, essays, and opinion pieces. It prided itself on offering in-depth analysis and research on important social, economic, and political issues of the time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The World''s Work magazine focused on promoting progressive ideas and social reform. It often covered topics such as labor rights, education, healthcare, and technological advancements, aiming to educate and engage its readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Influence and Readership' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'During its prime, The World''s Work magazine had a considerable influence on public opinion and policy debates. Its articles and editorials sparked discussions and helped shape the framework for social and political reforms in the United States and beyond.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine attracted a broad readership, including intellectuals, scholars, professionals, and individuals interested in understanding and exploring the changing world around them. Its reputation for quality journalism, insightful analysis, and thought-provoking content cemented its position as a leading publication of its time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Evolution and Decline' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'As the media landscape evolved, The World''s Work magazine faced challenges in adapting to new technologies and shifting reader preferences. The magazine underwent several rebrandings and format changes over the years, attempting to stay relevant in an increasingly competitive market.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'However, with the changing dynamics of the publishing industry and the decline of general interest magazines, The World''s Work magazine struggled to maintain its readership. It eventually ceased publication in 1932.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The legacy of The World''s Work magazine lives on as a testament to its dedication to informed journalism and its role in shaping public discourse during a transformative era.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

