VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A beloved teen magazine that influenced youth culture, offering fashion, beauty, and lifestyle content catering to young female readers.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'YM magazine, also known as *YoungMiss*, was a popular teen magazine that targeted young female readers. It provided a wide range of content, including fashion, beauty, lifestyle, and relationship advice.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### History and Publication' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'YM magazine was first published in 1932 by the Crowell-Collier Publishing Company. Initially titled "Miss Young''s Magazine," it aimed to cater to the interests and needs of young women. Over the years, the magazine went through several name changes before settling on "YM" in the late 1960s.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'YM magazine covered a vast array of topics relevant to its target audience. It offered fashion tips, trend reports, beauty advice, and health-related articles. The magazine included regular features such as "Dear YM," where readers could seek guidance on personal and relationship matters, and "Stars," which showcased interviews and profiles of popular celebrities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Popularity and Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'YM magazine gained a significant following during its publication and played a prominent role in youth culture. It provided a platform for young women to stay updated on the latest fashion and beauty trends, while also addressing important issues they faced in their daily lives. The magazine''s relatable content and relatable tone helped to establish YM as a trusted source of information and entertainment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Transformations and Cessation' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2000, YM magazine underwent a revamp in an attempt to attract a more mature audience. However, despite the changes, the magazine struggled to retain its readership and adapt to the digital age. In 2004, YM transitioned to a digital-only format, but ultimately ceased publication in 2004.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'### Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'YM magazine left a lasting impact on the teen magazine industry and the young women who grew up reading it. It provided teenage girls with a source of inspiration, knowledge, and entertainment, helping shape their tastes and aspirations.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

