VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A quarterly historical magazine dedicated to preserving North Yarmouth''s history, featuring profiles of notable residents, historic events, and local landmarks.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Old Times in North Yarmouth, Maine is a quarterly historical magazine that began publication in 1974.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is dedicated to preserving the history of North Yarmouth, a town in Cumberland County, Maine. Each issue of Old Times in North Yarmouth, Maine features articles on various aspects of the town''s history, including profiles of notable residents, coverage of historic events, and details of local landmarks and buildings.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its historical content, Old Times in North Yarmouth, Maine also includes updates on present-day happenings in North Yarmouth, along with features on local businesses and community events.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Old Times in North Yarmouth, Maine is published by the North Yarmouth Historical Society, a non-profit organization founded in 1970 to preserve and promote the history of the town. The magazine is made possible by a team of volunteers, including writers, editors, and photographers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Thanks to its dedication to local history and its knowledgeable contributors, Old Times in North Yarmouth, Maine has become a valuable resource for historians, genealogists, and anyone interested in learning more about the rich and colorful history of North Yarmouth.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

