VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine focused on the LGBTQ+ community, providing news, entertainment, and advocacy for transgender rights in the United States.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Outlook Media is a monthly magazine focused on the LGBTQ+ community, published in the United States. The magazine began in 1995 under the name ''Outlook Weekly'' and was originally distributed for free in Central Ohio.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covers a range of topics including news, politics, entertainment, and lifestyle issues related to the LGBTQ+ community. It also features interviews with activists, artists, and community leaders as well as opinion pieces written by members of the community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Outlook Media has won numerous awards for journalism and has been recognized for its coverage of issues affecting the LGBTQ+ community. The magazine has been particularly active in advocating for transgender rights and promoting visibility and acceptance of the transgender community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, Outlook Media also operates an online news website and a radio station. The magazine hosts events and fundraisers throughout the year, including the annual ''Pride of the Buckeye'' awards which recognize individuals who have made significant contributions to the LGBTQ+ community in Central Ohio.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, Outlook Media is recognized as one of the leading voices for the LGBTQ+ community in the United States, providing important news and analysis on issues affecting the community and celebrating its achievements and contributions.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Outlook
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Outlook', N'the-outlook', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A weekly magazine published in New York City from 1870-1935, known for its progressive stance on politics and society, and for its influential contributions to American journalism.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Outlook was a weekly magazine published in New York City from 1870 to 1935. Founded by a group of Congregationalist ministers, the magazine was known for its liberal and progressive stance on political and social issues.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Outlook covered a wide range of topics, including politics, literature, and the arts. It was particularly noted for its coverage of the women''s suffrage movement and the campaign for civil rights for African Americans.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its history, The Outlook featured contributions from many notable writers and public figures, including Theodore Roosevelt, Winston Churchill, and Mark Twain. The magazine also published both fiction and non-fiction books.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of The Outlook''s most significant contributions to American journalism was its creation of the "Outlook School of Journalism" in 1901. The school provided training and support for aspiring journalists, and many of its graduates went on to successful careers in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'As the 20th century progressed, The Outlook struggled to maintain its relevance in a rapidly changing media landscape, and its circulation declined. The magazine ultimately ceased publication in 1935, but its legacy lives on in the many writers and journalists who were inspired by its progressive values and commitment to social justice.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, The Outlook is remembered as an important publication in the history of American journalism, documenting the social and political changes of the late 19th and early 20th centuries and providing a platform for some of the most important writers and thinkers of the era.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- OutServe Magazine
