VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Official weekly magazine of the Assemblies of God USA, covering a range of Christian topics from a Pentecostal perspective.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'**Pentecostal Evangel** is the official weekly magazine of the Assemblies of God USA, one of the largest Pentecostal denominations in the world. The magazine is published in English and is based in Springfield, Missouri.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covers a range of topics related to the Christian faith and the Assemblies of God denomination. It includes news, commentary, feature articles, and theological reflections from a Pentecostal perspective.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Pentecostal Evangel was first published in 1913 as a newspaper called The Christian Evangel. It became a magazine in 1915, and was later renamed Pentecostal Evangel in 1919.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, Pentecostal Evangel also features online content, including articles, blogs, and multimedia resources. Its website also provides information on upcoming events, news from the Assemblies of God denomination, and opportunities for ministry and outreach.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, Pentecostal Evangel remains an important resource for members of the Assemblies of God and anyone interested in Pentecostal theology and practice. The magazine continues to offer thought-provoking content and engaging resources to inspire spiritual growth and renewal.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

