VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Celebrity and entertainment magazine published in the UK, known for its exclusive photographs and captivating coverage of popular culture.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'**People Today** was a celebrity and entertainment magazine published in the United Kingdom. The magazine covered a range of topics related to popular culture, including celebrity news, fashion, and lifestyle.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'People Today was first published in 1968 by the International Publishing Corporation, which later became IPC Media. The magazine was launched as a British version of the American magazine *People*.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, People Today developed a reputation for its in-depth celebrity interviews and insightful coverage of the entertainment industry. The magazine was known for featuring exclusive photographs and stories, as well as expert analysis and commentary.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1996, People Today was merged with another IPC Media title, **TVTODAY**, to form **TVTimes**. The new publication continued to cover entertainment and celebrity news, but with a greater emphasis on television programming.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, People Today remains an important part of the history of celebrity journalism in the United Kingdom. Its coverage of popular culture and entertainment provides a valuable snapshot of British society in the latter half of the 20th century.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

