VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A bodybuilding and fitness magazine featuring articles on nutrition, training and competition with a focus on athletes and enthusiasts.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'**Planet Muscle** was a bodybuilding and fitness magazine published from 2002 to 2009. The magazine featured articles on nutrition, supplementation, workout routines, and bodybuilding competitions.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Planet Muscle was founded by Robert Kennedy, who was also the founder of MuscleMag International, which was among the best-selling bodybuilding magazines of all time. The magazine''s content was geared towards bodybuilding enthusiasts and athletes, and was written by leading experts in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Planet Muscle featured a wide range of topics related to bodybuilding and fitness, including training tips, supplement reviews, athlete profiles, and in-depth coverage of bodybuilding competitions. The magazine was known for its high-quality photography, which showcased the physiques of the world''s top bodybuilders.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its popularity, Planet Muscle ceased publication in 2009, citing declining sales and the economic recession. Today, Planet Muscle is remembered as an important part of the bodybuilding and fitness industry, which influenced and inspired readers to pursue fitness and bodybuilding at the highest level.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Play
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
