VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An American motorcycle magazine that covers custom bikes and motorcycle lifestyle and culture.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse is an American motorcycle magazine that was first published in 1979. The magazine is known for its coverage of custom motorcycles, as well as motorcycle lifestyle and culture.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse magazine was founded by Dennis Stemp and David Snow. The first issue of the magazine was published in October 1979, and featured a custom Harley Davidson on the cover.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse has been published on a monthly basis throughout its history, and has become one of the most popular motorcycle magazines in the United States.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse magazine primarily covers custom motorcycles, including Harley Davidsons, choppers, bobbers, and cafe racers. The magazine also covers motorcycle lifestyle and culture, including events, rallies, and charity rides.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse occasionally features road tests and reviews of new motorcycles, but its primary focus is on custom motorcycles. The magazine also includes articles on motorcycle safety, maintenance, and customization techniques.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Audience and Reception' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse magazine primarily targets the motorcycle enthusiast market. The magazine is popular among riders and collectors of custom motorcycles, as well as enthusiasts of the motorcycle lifestyle and culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse has been generally well-received by readers and critics alike. The magazine is praised for its high-quality photography and in-depth coverage of custom motorcycles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Iron Horse magazine has become a staple of the American motorcycle industry. The magazine has helped to promote custom motorcycles as a serious art form and cultural movement.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'While the magazine has faced some criticism for its focusing exclusively on custom motorcycles, Iron Horse continues to be a popular and influential publication in the motorcycle community.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Islamic Monthly
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Islamic Monthly', N'the-islamic-monthly', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A North American magazine covering current events, culture, and views related to the global Muslim community.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly is a North American magazine that covers current events, culture, and views related to the global Muslim community.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly was founded in 2011 by Arsalan Iftikhar, a human rights lawyer and commentator on issues of Islam and Muslims. The magazine began as an online publication before expanding to print.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly covers a wide range of topics related to Islam and the Muslim world, including current events, politics, culture, and arts. The magazine has featured interviews with prominent Muslim figures, as well as commentary and analysis from both Muslim and non-Muslim writers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly also publishes articles on topics related to the intersection of Islam and modernity, such as science, technology, and social media. The magazine has been known to address sensitive and controversial subjects such as women''s rights, LGBTQ+ issues, and sectarianism within the Muslim community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Audience and Reception' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly targets a North American Muslim audience, as well as anyone interested in issues related to the global Muslim community. The magazine has been praised for providing a platform for diverse Muslim voices and perspectives, especially those that are often excluded from mainstream media.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly has been recognized for its contributions to promoting greater understanding and appreciation of the Muslim world. The magazine has received numerous awards, including the American Muslim Consumer Conference''s Best Media Outlet Award in 2012 and the Muslim Public Affairs Council''s Voices of Courage and Conscience Award in 2014.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since its founding, The Islamic Monthly has become an influential publication in the North American Muslim community. The magazine has been at the forefront of discussions on contemporary issues affecting Muslims, and has challenged stereotypes and misconceptions about Islam and Muslim societies.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Islamic Monthly has also inspired the launch of other Muslim-focused publications, helping to create a broader media landscape for Muslim voices and perspectives.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Islamic Review
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Islamic Review', N'islamic-review', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly English-language Islamic publication offering articles, commentary and analysis on religious and social issues affecting Muslims across the globe.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Islamic Review Magazine, also known as ''Al-Adab Al-Islami'' in Arabic, is a monthly English-language publication that was first established in 1913 in London, United Kingdom. It was founded by Khwaja Kamaluddin, a student of Mirza Ghulam Ahmad, the founder of the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is widely regarded as one of the most influential Islamic periodicals in the world. It offers a range of articles, commentary and analysis on various aspects of the Islamic world, including religious issues, culture, politics, economics, and interfaith relations.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The editorial policy of Islamic Review Magazine is based on promoting peace, inter-religious dialogue and understanding among societies. It presents a positive image of Islam to the wider world, and encourages constructive debates and discussions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Islamic Review Magazine has a readership that spans across the globe. It features articles by renowned scholars, Islamic experts and prominent figures from the Muslim community and beyond. The magazine also provides original research and book reviews that contribute to the development of Islamic scholarship.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its long history, Islamic Review Magazine has gone through various changes to reflect the current state of the global Islamic landscape. Initially, the magazine mainly focused on the Ahmadiyya sect of Islam, but over the years, it expanded its scope to cover issues affecting Muslims worldwide.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The headquarters of Islamic Review Magazine is located in London, with distribution made worldwide. Despite various challenges, including a brief interruption during World War II, Islamic Review Magazine has retained its position as one of the leading English-language Islamic periodicals in the world.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- It is. A Magazine for Abstract Art
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'It is. A Magazine for Abstract Art', N'it-is-a-magazine-for-abstract-art', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A quarterly magazine published between 1958 and 1978 that focused on promoting and displaying abstract art covering work from emerging artists as well as established figures.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## It is. A Magazine for Abstract Art{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'It is. A Magazine for Abstract Art, also known simply as It is., is a quarterly magazine dedicated to abstract art. It was first published in 1958 by artist, poet and editor, Robert Indiana. The magazine was published until 1978 when its last issue was released.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'It is. was one of the most influential art magazines of the 1960s. The magazine aimed to provide a platform for abstract art and to promote its significance in the contemporary art world. It featured work from emerging abstract artists as well as established figures in the art world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine placed a strong emphasis on the visual presentation of abstract art. Its minimal layout and design approach favored the use of white space, sans-serif typeface, and a limited color palette.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Contributors to It is. included some of the most significant artists, writers, and thinkers of the time, such as Ellsworth Kelly, Ad Reinhardt, and Frank Stella. It also published works of criticism, poetry, and philosophy.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, It is. remains a significant artifact of the period in which it was published and has been featured in various art exhibitions and publications. The magazine is recognized for its contribution to the abstract art movement and continues to be a point of reference for contemporary art scholars and enthusiasts.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Jazz Review
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Jazz Review', N'the-jazz-review', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A now-defunct quarterly magazine dedicated to jazz music and culture, renowned for its intellectual approach and contributions from prominent jazz writers and musicians.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Jazz Review was a quarterly magazine that was first published in New York City in 1958. The magazine was founded by Nat Hentoff, a renowned jazz historian, author, and critic, and was published until 1961.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Jazz Review was dedicated solely to jazz music and its culture. The magazine provided extensive coverage of jazz music''s history, reviews of albums, concerts and festivals, interviews with prominent jazz musicians, and essays on jazz criticism.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its publication period, The Jazz Review remained a prestigious forum for jazz musicians and intellectuals. The magazine featured articles by renowned jazz writers such as LeRoi Jones, Amiri Baraka, Martin Williams and Ralph Ellison. It also offered literary contributions from celebrated writers such as Jack Kerouac and Kenneth Rexroth.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Jazz Review was known for its sophisticated and intellectual approach to covering jazz music. The magazine was praised for its analytical tone, original research, and insightful reviews. The Jazz Review was considered as a premier journal for jazz scholarship and intellectual discourse.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, The Jazz Review remains an important source for jazz music history and criticism. Many of its articles and essays have been reprinted in subsequent collections, and the magazine is recognized as one of the most influential publications in jazz music''s history.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

