VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A peer-reviewed academic journal that focuses on biomedical research conducted by scientists at the National Institutes of Health.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Journal of NIH Research{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Journal of NIH Research is a bi-monthly peer-reviewed academic journal that focuses on biomedical research conducted by scientists at the National Institutes of Health (NIH). The journal was established in 1989 and is published by the NIH itself.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Journal of NIH Research publishes original research articles, review articles, and brief communications related to a wide range of biomedical research topics. The journal''s editorial team consists primarily of current and former NIH scientists, ensuring a high level of expertise in the topics covered.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The journal aims to provide a platform for the publication of cutting-edge research conducted by NIH scientists, and to facilitate the dissemination of NIH-funded research to a wider audience. As such, the journal is open-access, meaning that all articles are freely available to read online.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Journal of NIH Research is indexed in several academic databases, including PubMed and Scopus, and has a high impact factor within the scientific community. The journal''s rigorous peer-review process ensures that all articles published in the journal meet high academic standards.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

