VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A quarterly publication featuring local content, photography, and articles focused on Milford, Connecticut.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Milford Magazine is a quarterly publication based in Milford, Connecticut, United States. The magazine focuses on the local community and features a range of content covering topics such as history, culture, lifestyle, and events.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was first published in 2003 and has since become an important source of information for residents and visitors to Milford. It is distributed throughout the region and is also available online.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Milford Magazine is renowned for its high-quality photography and informative articles. The magazine prides itself on capturing the essence of life in Milford and providing readers with a glimpse into the town''s unique character.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Milford Magazine features a range of content, including interviews with prominent community members, coverage of local events, and features on businesses and organizations in the area. The magazine also frequently publishes articles on Milford''s rich history and culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Milford Magazine has won numerous awards over the years, including recognition for its exceptional photography and design. The magazine has also been praised for its commitment to community journalism, bringing attention to local issues and events that might otherwise go unnoticed.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, Milford Magazine continues to be a valuable resource for the Milford community, providing a platform for local voices and celebrating the town''s achievements and character.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Millennial Harbinger
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Millennial Harbinger', N'the-millennial-harbinger', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly religious publication founded by Alexander Campbell in 1830, playing an important role in the development of the Restoration Movement.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Millennial Harbinger was a religious magazine founded by Alexander Campbell in 1830 in Bethany, Virginia (now West Virginia), United States. The magazine was published monthly and focused primarily on religious topics.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Millennial Harbinger played an important role in the development of the Restoration Movement, which sought to restore the church to its original New Testament form. Campbell''s teachings and writings, including those in the Millennial Harbinger, helped to shape the beliefs and practices of the movement.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine featured articles by Campbell and other Restoration Movement leaders, as well as articles by writers from other denominations. The content of the magazine covered a wide range of religious topics, including theology, history, and current events. The Millennial Harbinger also included book reviews, poetry, and letters from readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine ceased publication in 1870, but its impact on religious thought and practice continued to be felt for decades to come. Today, the Millennial Harbinger is recognized as an important historical document, offering insights into the beliefs and values of the Restoration Movement during its formative years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively short publication history, the Millennial Harbinger remains an important source of information and inspiration for scholars, historians, and religious leaders interested in the Restoration Movement and its impact on American religious life.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Milo
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Milo', N'milo', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A conservative and libertarian American magazine covering politics, culture, and current events, known for its controversial viewpoints.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Milo (2004-2018) was an American magazine which covered politics, culture, and current events from a conservative and libertarian perspective. The magazine was founded in 2004 by L. Brent Bozell III as a conservative alternative to existing news and opinion publications.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s name was inspired by the ancient Greek wrestler Milo of Croton, known for his immense strength and longevity. The magazine''s founders sought to emulate Milo''s spirit of strength and endurance in their coverage of political and cultural issues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Milo''s content included articles on politics, economics, foreign policy, culture, and art, as well as book reviews and original fiction. The magazine''s writers and contributors were a mix of established conservative or libertarian pundits, academics, and journalists, as well as rising stars in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine generated controversy with its outspoken stance on issues such as immigration, multiculturalism, and political correctness, which often put it at odds with mainstream media outlets and academic institutions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2018, the magazine ceased publication due to financial difficulties. However, its influence can still be felt today in the continuing debates over free speech, identity politics, and the future of conservatism in America.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

