VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A men''s magazine published in the US from 1951 to 1967 featuring fashion, sports, entertainment, and the annual ''Modern Man Awards''.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Man was a men''s magazine that was published in the United States from 1951 to 1967. {{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a range of topics related to men''s interests, including fashion, style, sports, and entertainment. It was known for its cutting-edge design and photography, as well as its frank and sometimes controversial editorial content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Man was founded by a group of publishers who had worked on a previous men''s magazine called Stag. The new publication was intended to be a more modern and sophisticated version of Stag, and it quickly gained a following among young, urban men.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its editorial content, Modern Man was known for hosting a series of annual "Modern Man Awards," which honored men in various fields for their achievements and contributions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'During its run, Modern Man published articles by a number of notable writers, including Jack Kerouac, Norman Mailer, and Ray Bradbury.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its success, Modern Man faced declining readership in the late 1960s, and it was eventually merged with another men''s magazine, Cavalier, in 1967.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, Modern Man is remembered as an important part of the cultural landscape of the 1950s and 1960s. Its coverage of fashion, style, and entertainment provides a window into the interests and values of men during this era.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

