VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A college prep magazine providing guidance to high school students on college readiness, admissions, financial aid, and scholarships in the US.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'NextStepU is a quarterly print and online magazine aimed at high school students in the United States who are preparing for college. The magazine was founded in 2005 and is published by Carnegie Communications, a digital marketing and recruitment company based in Westford, Massachusetts.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine provides guidance and advice to high school students on a variety of topics related to college admissions and the college experience. The topics covered in the magazine include college search and selection, college readiness, financial aid, scholarships, and the college application process.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to the magazine, NextStepU also provides an array of online resources and tools to help high school students plan for college. These resources include interactive planning tools, virtual campus tours, career advice, and scholarship search engines.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'NextStepU is distributed free of charge to high schools across the United States, and the magazine''s online version is available to anyone with internet access. The magazine has won several awards for its content and design, including a Gold Award from the Association of Marketing and Communications Professionals.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Nickelodeon Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Nickelodeon Magazine', N'nickelodeon-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A children''s print magazine featuring articles, comics, and content related to popular Nickelodeon television shows in the US.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Nickelodeon Magazine{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nickelodeon Magazine was a print magazine published by Nickelodeon, a cable television network aimed at children. The magazine primarily targeted children aged 6-14, and featured various articles, comics, and other content related to popular Nickelodeon television shows.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was first published in 1993 and ceased publication in 2009, with a total of 216 issues released over its 16-year run. During its peak, the magazine had a circulation of over 1 million copies, making it one of the most popular children''s magazines in the United States.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Nickelodeon Magazine typically included a mix of features and columns, covering a range of topics related to Nickelodeon shows and popular culture. The magazine also included comics featuring characters from popular Nicktoons such as "Ren & Stimpy," "Rugrats," and "SpongeBob SquarePants."' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its success, declining readership and the rise of digital media eventually led to the magazine''s cancellation in 2009. Nickelodeon continued to produce other digital content targeted towards children, including websites and mobile apps.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nickelodeon Magazine won several awards during its run, including numerous Parents'' Choice Awards and a National Magazine Award in 2006 for General Excellence in the category of Under 12.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its cancellation, Nickelodeon Magazine remains a nostalgic touchstone for many individuals who grew up in the 1990s and 2000s. The magazine''s blend of humor, pop culture commentary, and Nicktoon-based comics continue to be remembered fondly by many in the current generation.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Night Sky
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Night Sky', N'night-sky', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine for stargazing enthusiasts featuring articles, reviews and sky charts on astronomy-related topics published in the US.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Night Sky magazine is a monthly magazine published by Kalmbach Media, a Wisconsin-based publishing company specializing in hobbyist magazines. The magazine primarily caters to hobbyists interested in astronomy and stargazing.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was first published in 1935 under the name The Sky. Over the years, the magazine has incorporated several other astronomy-related publications, including Deep Sky, Sky & Telescope, and the Australian publication Sky & Space.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Night Sky Magazine features a mix of astronomy-related articles, reviews of telescopes and other equipment, and star maps and sky charts for stargazing enthusiasts. The magazine also includes astrophotography tips and techniques, advice on dark-sky locations for observing the stars, and profiles of notable astronomers and contributions to the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Night Sky magazine has won several awards for its content and design, including the "Best Consumer Astronomy Magazine" award from the International Astronomical Union in 2017.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also maintains a website which offers additional content and resources for readers, including interactive star charts, news reports on astronomical events and discoveries, and a forum for readers to share tips, techniques, and experiences.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Night Sky Magazine has played an important role in popularizing astronomy and stargazing as a hobby, particularly in the United States. The magazine''s blend of accessible writing and high-quality images and illustrations has helped make stargazing and astronomy more accessible and engaging for hobbyists of all ages and experience levels.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Nine-O-One Network
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Nine-O-One Network', N'nine-o-one-network', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A defunct print magazine featuring articles, interviews, and other content related to the Nine-O-One Network''s shows and personalities in Memphis, USA.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nine-O-One Network was a print magazine published by Nine-O-One Network, a Memphis-based television network. The magazine primarily targeted viewers in the network''s local Memphis market, and featured various articles, interviews, and other content related to the network''s shows and personalities.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was first published in 1976 and ceased publication in 1991, with a total of 128 issues released over its 15-year run. During its peak, the magazine had a circulation of around 25,000 copies, making it one of the most popular local television magazines in the Memphis area.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of Nine-O-One Network Magazine typically included a mix of features and columns, covering a range of topics related to Nine-O-One Network shows and personalities. The magazine also included interviews with local and national celebrities, as well as coverage of local events and personalities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its success, declining advertising revenue eventually led to the magazine''s cancellation in 1991. Nine-O-One Network continued to produce other television content targeted towards viewers in the Memphis area, including news and entertainment programming.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively brief run, Nine-O-One Network Magazine remains an important artifact of Memphis television history. The magazine''s blend of coverage of local events, personalities, and celebrities, as well as its insider access to Nine-O-One Network shows and personalities, provide a unique window into the television and entertainment industry in Memphis in the 1970s and 1980s. The magazine is also valued as a collector''s item for fans of the network and its shows.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- No Depression
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'No Depression', N'no-depression', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A quarterly music magazine featuring in-depth coverage of roots music and lesser-known artists, as well as online media and live events.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'No Depression is a quarterly magazine dedicated to covering roots music, including Americana, folk, blues, and country, as well as contemporary artists who draw from these traditions. {{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Founded in Seattle, Washington in 1995 by co-editors Peter Blackstock and Grant Alden, No Depression originally began as a fanzine that aimed to chronicle the thriving alt-country and roots music scene in the Pacific Northwest. The magazine''s name is a reference to A.P. Carter''s 1927 recording "No Depression in Heaven," which has become a touchstone for traditional American music.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'No Depression has gained a reputation for its thoughtful and in-depth writing on roots music, as well as its commitment to highlighting lesser-known artists who may not receive coverage in mainstream music outlets. The magazine has featured interviews and essays with musicians including Gillian Welch, Wilco, Lucinda Williams, and Steve Earle, as well as up-and-coming artists who have gone on to gain wider recognition.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to print publishing, No Depression has expanded into online media with the creation of its website, which features reviews, interviews, and original content. The magazine also sponsors live events and festivals, including the annual No Depression Festival in St. Louis, Missouri.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'No Depression has been recognized with several awards, including the Utne Reader''s Independent Press Award for Arts Coverage in 2002 and 2004. The magazine''s archives are now housed at the University of North Carolina-Chapel Hill''s Southern Folklife Collection.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'No Depression has been influential in shaping the discourse around roots music in the United States and beyond, and its coverage has helped to raise awareness of a wide range of artists and styles. The magazine has spawned a community of like-minded roots music enthusiasts, including musicians, fans, and writers, who continue to work towards the preservation and promotion of traditional American music.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- North & South
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'North & South', N'north-and-south', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine focused on New Zealand culture, history, and current affairs, with a particular emphasis on the North-South divide.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'North & South was a monthly magazine published in New Zealand, and focused on New Zealand culture, history, and current affairs with a particular emphasis on the country''s North-South divide.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'First published in 1986 by journalist Robyn Langwell and photographer Chris Bourke, North & South appealed to a wide audience, including readers interested in politics, social issues, and lifestyle trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its feature articles, North & South published regular columns on topics such as health, travel, and food, as well as reviews of books, films, and television programs. The magazine was known for its high-quality journalism and award-winning writing.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'North & South went through several ownership changes during its 30-year run, and was ultimately acquired by Bauer Media Group in 2019. However, in December 2020, Bauer Media announced that it would be closing North & South due to declining advertising revenue and the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic. The magazine''s final issue was published in January 2021.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its closure, North & South remains a significant part of New Zealand publishing history and continues to be remembered for its contributions to journalism and the arts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Awards and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'North & South received numerous awards over the course of its run, including several Qantas Media Awards, New Zealand''s premier journalism awards. Notable accolades include Best Magazine Design, Best Investigative Journalism, and Best Cover. In 2015, North & South won Magazine of the Year at the Canon Media Awards.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Northeast Boating Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Northeast Boating Magazine', N'northeast-boating-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A six times annually published American boating magazine covering cruising, fishing, and water-related activities in the northeastern US and southeast Canada.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northeast Boating Magazine is an American boating publication headquartered in Essex, Connecticut. Founded in 1971, the magazine covers boating, fishing, and water-related activities in the northeastern United States and southeast Canada.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is published six times per year, and each issue features articles on cruising destinations, boat tests and reviews, fishing techniques, maintenance, and safety. Northeast Boating Magazine also includes classified ads for boats and boating-related products, as well as a calendar of upcoming boating events.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northeast Boating Magazine has a loyal following among boating enthusiasts in the northeastern United States, and has been recognized for its high-quality journalism and photography. The magazine has won several awards from the Boating Writers International, including the Award of Merit and the Best Boating Photography award.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Northeast Boating Magazine has undergone several changes in ownership and editorial direction. In 2018, the magazine was acquired by Power & Motoryacht Magazine, a division of AIM Media. Despite these changes, Northeast Boating Magazine continues to be a popular and respected source of information for boaters in the northeastern United States.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Northern Junket
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Northern Junket', N'northern-junket', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A US magazine devoted to traditional crafts, folk art and rural living, known for its high-quality photography and writing, published from 1965 to 1994.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northern Junket was a magazine published in the United States that focused on traditional crafts, folk art, and rural living. Founded in 1965 by Celeste and Fred Ray, the magazine was headquartered in Rochester, Minnesota.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine published six issues annually and featured articles on a wide range of topics, including quilting, woodworking, basketry, and home gardening. Each issue also included recipes, book reviews, and news about upcoming events related to traditional crafts and folk art.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northern Junket gained a loyal following among readers interested in traditional crafts and rural living, and was known for its high-quality photography and writing. The magazine also sponsored several crafts conferences and festivals, which drew attendees from around the country.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1985, Northern Junket was sold to a new publisher, who continued to operate the magazine until its final issue was published in 1994. Despite its relatively short run, Northern Junket remains a significant part of the history of traditional crafts and folk art in the United States.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Northwest Mountaineering Journal
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Northwest Mountaineering Journal', N'northwest-mountaineering-journal', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A quarterly publication for mountaineering, hiking and climbing in the Pacific Northwest region of the US founded by Fred Beckey in 1948, featuring articles on mountaineering routes, gear reviews, and interviews with climbers.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northwest Mountaineering Journal was a quarterly publication focusing on mountaineering, hiking, and climbing covering Pacific Northwest region of the United States. The magazine was published in Seattle, Washington, and was established in 1948 by a group of mountaineers led by Fred Beckey. {{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The founders of the magazine aimed to promote and share the rising popularity of mountaineering in the 1940s in the US. The magazine''s intent has always been to encourage people to master mountaineering skills, discuss routes, share climbing experiences, and cultivate a sense of community among Northwest climbers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of the magazine included articles on mountaineering routes, gear reviews, interviews with prominent climbers, and news about upcoming climbing events. Moreover, it contributed to promoting outdoor activities in the Pacific Northwest region by featuring articles on hiking and camping, book reviews, photography, and artwork.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northwest Mountaineering Journal had many contributors with experiences ranging from enthusiasts to leading climbers and mountaineers, all providing their expertise. Readers could expect a high level of professional writing and reliable information on all topics related to climbing and hiking in the Pacific Northwest.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine continued to publish until 1986 but then ceased edition due to financial constraints. However, it remains a significant part of the history of mountaineering and outdoor recreation in the Pacific Northwest for over thirty-eight years.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Northwestern Lumberman
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Northwestern Lumberman', N'northwestern-lumberman', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly trade publication covering the forest products industry in the Pacific Northwest region of the United States from 1890 to 1963.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northwestern Lumberman was a monthly trade publication focusing on the forest products industry in the Pacific Northwest region of the United States. The magazine was published in Portland, Oregon, and was established in 1890 by R. W. Hawley.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a wide range of topics related to the lumber and forest products industry, including news and updates on mill operations, logging, transportation, and international trade. It also published articles on forest management, technology, and labor relations.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northwestern Lumberman was known for its extensive coverage of the Pacific Northwest timber industry, which was one of the largest in the world during the 20th century. It was an important source of news and information for the industry professionals, including loggers, sawmill operators, and traders.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, the magazine expanded its coverage beyond the Pacific Northwest to include other regions of the United States and Canada. It also included articles on topics such as woodworking, construction, and design.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Northwestern Lumberman continued to publish until 1963 when it merged with another publication to form Western Wood Products. Despite its relatively short existence, Northwestern Lumberman is considered an important historical resource for understanding the development of the timber industry in the Pacific Northwest region of the United States.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Nose
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Nose', N'the-nose', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A literary magazine bringing the avant-garde to San Francisco''s counterculture scene from 1968 to 1980.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nose was a literary magazine published twice a year in the United States from 1968 to 1980. The magazine was based in San Francisco and focused on publishing experimental and avant-garde literature and art.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nose was founded in 1968 by a group of writers and artists of the San Francisco Bay area. The magazine''s editorial board comprised various established artists and poets who were champions of the counterculture movement, including Bob Kaufman and Neeli Cherkovski.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nose published works of emerging authors, including Charles Bukowski, Bobbie Louise Hawkins, and Jack Micheline. The magazine featured avant-garde prose, poetry, and art along with interviews with counterculture artists, literary reviews, and essays on art and politics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s main motivation was to be a platform for the avant-garde, experimental, and marginal in literature and art. The magazine was particularly interested in work that pushed boundaries, broke with traditional literary forms, and embodied a sense of resistance and rebellion.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively short run, The Nose became an influential magazine that paved the way for experimental literature and art. The magazine''s legacy was still felt in San Francisco''s literary scene in the 1970s and beyond.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Nuestro
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Nuestro', N'nuestro', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A pioneering magazine promoting Latin American culture and civil rights advocacy in the United States from 1940 to 1961.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nuestro was a pioneering magazine aimed at the Latin American community in the United States. The magazine was published in English and Spanish from 1940 to 1961 and was based in Los Angeles.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nuestro was established by Sonny King, an African-American jazz singer, and activist who recognized the lack of representation of Latin Americans in mainstream media at the time. The magazine aimed to create a platform for Latin American voices, celebrating the culture and achievements of the Latin American community in the United States.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nuestro''s content was diverse and covered a broad range of topics that were relevant to the Latin American community, including politics, art, literature, and entertainment. Over the years, the magazine featured contributions from a wide range of writers, artists, and politicians, including Frida Kahlo, Langston Hughes, and Cesar Chavez.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nuestro was known for its advocacy of civil rights and social justice issues. The magazine played an important role in shaping the public discourse and challenging stereotypes associated with Latin American culture. Nuestro also showcased emerging talent in literature and art and provided a platform for Latin American writers and artists who were often overlooked by mainstream publishers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively short run, Nuestro became an influential publication that paved the way for other Latin American publications in the United States. The magazine''s legacy was felt in Latin American communities across the United States, and its contributions to promoting social justice and fighting prejudice and discrimination continue to inspire generations.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- NutriMag
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'NutriMag', N'nutrimag', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly health and wellness magazine providing practical tips and evidence-based advice for maintaining a healthy body and mind.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'NutriMag is a health and wellness magazine that provides information about nutrition, healthy living, and fitness. The magazine is published monthly in the United States and has a significant readership in the health and wellness industry.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'NutriMag was established in 2005 by a group of health and wellness enthusiasts who recognized the need for a trusted source of information about healthy living. The magazine''s content is designed to educate readers about the benefits of a healthy lifestyle and to provide practical tips and advice for maintaining a healthy body and mind.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covers a diverse range of topics related to health and wellness, including nutrition, exercise, mental health, alternative medicine, and healthy lifestyle choices. NutriMag regularly features interviews with experts in the health and wellness field, as well as success stories from individuals who have achieved their health and fitness goals.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'NutriMag''s articles are well-researched and evidence-based, so readers can trust that the information provided is accurate and reliable. The magazine also provides readers with links to additional resources and references for further reading.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, NutriMag has an online presence and also publishes an e-newsletter. The magazine''s website features additional articles, blogs, and videos related to health and wellness, allowing readers to access the latest information and stay up-to-date with the latest trends in the health and wellness industry.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Nuts & Bolts of PBM
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Nuts & Bolts of PBM', N'the-nuts-and-bolts-of-pbm', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A bi-monthly trade magazine providing analysis and insights on the pharmacy benefit management (PBM) industry for professionals and stakeholders.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nuts & Bolts of PBM is a trade magazine in the United States that focuses on the pharmacy benefit management (PBM) industry. PBMs are intermediaries between health insurers and pharmacies, primarily responsible for negotiating drug prices, processing and handling pharmacy claims, and managing drug formularies.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nuts & Bolts of PBM was established in 1996 and is published bi-monthly. The magazine is primarily aimed at PBM executives and professionals, as well as healthcare executives, policymakers, and other stakeholders in the healthcare industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s content is focused on the PBM industry and provides readers with in-depth information on the latest trends, policy developments, and business strategies in the industry. The Nuts & Bolts of PBM also provides detailed analysis of PBM market data, industry research, and legislative and regulatory affairs.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The publication prides itself on providing insightful and reliable information to help PBMs and other stakeholders make informed decisions and navigate the complex and evolving PBM industry. The Nuts & Bolts of PBM is known for its well-researched articles, data analysis, and expert commentary, and is considered a leading voice in the PBM industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, The Nuts & Bolts of PBM has an online presence, providing access to additional resources and the latest news and updates in the PBM industry. The magazine''s website also features a job board and advertising opportunities for businesses in the PBM industry.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

