VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American lifestyle publication focusing on New York City''s culture, luxury real estate, fine dining, fashion, and entertainment.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Gotham Magazine{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gotham Magazine is an American lifestyle publication centered around New York City. It is owned by Modern Luxury Media, a prominent luxury lifestyle media company in the United States that specializes in publishing city-specific magazines. The magazine focuses on the city''s vibrant culture, showcasing everything from fashion, beauty, and wellness to shopping, dining, nightlife, and real estate.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History and Ownership' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gotham Magazine was launched in 2001 as part of the GreenGale Publishing LLC (formerly known as Niche Media Holdings), which was later acquired by Modern Luxury Media in 2017. The company''s portfolio includes several other city-focused lifestyle publications such as Boston Common, Capitol File, and LA Confidential. The magazine''s editorial approach blends local interest stories with coverage of national and international trends, reflecting New York City''s status as a global hub.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine provides in-depth features about notable personalities, entrepreneurs, artists, and philanthropists who shape the city''s cultural landscape. Aside from its people-centric content, Gotham Magazine is known for its spotlight on high-end lifestyle, including luxury real estate, fine dining, fashion, and entertainment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Frequency and Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gotham Magazine is published eight times a year, with spring, summer, fall, winter, and special editions, including the influential "Men''s Issue" and "Women of Influence" editions. It is distributed to targeted locations in Manhattan, including luxury towers, private clubs, five-star hotels, private jet terminals, and cultural institutions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Digital Presence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print version, Gotham Magazine maintains a robust online presence through its website. This platform allows the magazine to reach an even broader audience and provide up-to-the-minute coverage and behind-the-scenes content of special events, exclusive parties, and glamorous galas in the city.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Notable Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gotham Magazine does not just focus on personalities and events but also embraces philanthropy. Its annual "Altruist of the Year" honors individuals who have made significant contributions to society and made a positive impact.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'##Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Gotham Magazine has become a powerful influence in New York City''s media landscape, playing a significant role in shaping public opinion about the city''s lifestyle and culture. It remains a credible source of information and a definitive guide for residents and visitors interested in the city''s luxurious side.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gourmet Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Gourmet Magazine', N'gourmet-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American food and lifestyle publication, known for culinary writings, recipes, and influence on food journalism.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gourmet Magazine was an American food and lifestyle publication that was renowned for its use of lavish food photography, perceptive writings, and a sophisticated tone. The magazine focused on food and drink, recipes, travel, restaurants, and entertaining.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History and Ownership' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gourmet Magazine was first published in January 1941 by Condé Nast Publications, a subsidiary of Advance Publications which is a leading media company operating in the print, digital, TV, and technology industries. The magazine was marketed as a publication "for bon vivants," and it quickly gained popularity for its elegant presentation and editorial content. Sadly, after a 68-year run, Gourmet Magazine ceased publication in November 2009 owing to economic circumstances.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gourmet Magazine was celebrated for its rich and engrossing features, from historical culinary journeys to reviews of the newest restaurants. It catered to those interested in cooking, dining, and the culture of food. Its exemplary recipes, known for their precision and ease of understanding, were a mainstay in its content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Frequency and Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gourmet Magazine was published monthly before it was discontinued. It had a strong nationwide distribution, reaching millions of homes and businesses. It was available on newsstands and through subscriptions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Digital Presence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Even after its print edition ceased publication, Gourmet said goodbye to its print tradition but continued its legacy in the digital space. Gourmet.com, the magazine''s online counterpart, continued to supply readers with carefully curated content centered around food and lifestyle. However, the site was eventually rerouted to Epicurious, another Condé Nast food and recipe website.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Contributions to Food Journalism ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gourmet Magazine presented an elevated perspective of the culinary world and profoundly contributed to the shape of modern food journalism. It brought attention to the sociopolitical issues surrounding food, embedded narrative journalism into its edibles features, and portrayed the beauty of culinary artistry through meticulously staged food photography.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Notable Personalities' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Under Ruth Reichl''s editorship from 1999 to 2009, Gourmet Magazine experienced a significant transformation. The accomplished food writer and critic exerted notable influence on the magazine, adding depth with features on the intersection of food and social issues.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Grecian Guild Pictorial
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Grecian Guild Pictorial', N'grecian-guild-pictorial', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Pioneering American gay men''s physique magazine, key contributor to post-war gay subculture.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Overview{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grecian Guild Pictorial was a pioneering American gay men''s magazine that played a key role during the post-war gay culture in the United States. Launched in the late 1950s by H. Lynn Womack, the publication was largely pictorial and often featured erotic content, which made it immensely popular amongst the gay community of the era.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was first published by Washington based Guild Press, founded by H. Lynn Womack, an entrepreneur with a doctoral degree in English. Guild Press primarily published male physique magazines, amongst which Grecian Guild Pictorial was one of the flagships.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grecian Guild Pictorial was a physique photography magazine, showcasing artistic images of muscular men, often with classical or historical themed settings. It promoted fitness, bodybuilding, and celebrated the male form. Though physique magazines of the era were typically not expressly gay periodicals, by presenting homoerotic imagistic content, Grecian Guild Pictorial catered to a largely gay audience.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Sociological Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'During the 1950s and 1960s, where open sexuality was harshly stigmatized, Grecian Guild Pictorial provided an outlet for gay individuals to discreetly explore and connect with their sexuality. The magazine thus significantly contributed to the gay subculture of that era.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legal Issues' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H. Lynn Womack and Guild Press faced multiple legal issues due to the erotic content of their publications. In 1963, the United States Supreme Court handled a noteworthy obscenity case involving one of Guild Press''s titles. Winning the case set a precedent allowing gay erotica to be mailed, which eventually led to more openness in the portrayal of homoerotic content in magazines.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Green Bag (1889–1914)
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Green Bag (1889–1914)', N'the-Green-bag-1889–1914', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American legal journal from 1889–1914 aimed at making law accessible to general readers.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Green Bag (1889–1914) was an American legal journal addressed to the general reader. Founded by Horace W. Fuller, the Editor of the Central Law Journal, the magazine aimed to make the law more accessible to the public with its straightforward and lucid articles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Initiated in 1889, The Green Bag was established in Boston, Massachusetts, by a group of legal scholars led by Horace W. Fuller. This general-interest legal publication was relatively unusual for its time, attempting to make the law and its intricacies accessible to non-lawyers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Green Bag was explicitly intended for non-lawyers and targeted a broad readership. It featured scholarly articles and legal opinion pieces written in a less formal tone than traditional legal texts. These articles discussed contemporary legal issues, prominent court cases, and profiles of eminent judges and attorneys.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was distinctively recognized for its ''Court of Last Resort,'' which analyzed high-profile legal disputes in a comprehensible language for the layman. This blend of scholarship with public appeal was a unique feature of The Green Bag and its lasting legacy.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence and Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively short lifespan, The Green Bag profoundly impacted the public understanding of the law. By making the law accessible to everyday readers, it bridge the gap between legal comprehension and the layman, prompting discourse about legal matters beyond professional circles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Revival' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1997, The Green Bag was revived under the full title ''The Green Bag: An Entertaining Journal of Law.'' This resurrection was in the spirit of the original publication, providing scholarly yet friendly perspectives on legal studies to the public.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Green Guide
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Green Guide', N'the-green-guide', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Environmental magazine featuring practical solutions for sustainable living and responsible consumption.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Green Guide is an environmental magazine which offers practical advice on green living. The magazine targets a readership interested in sustainable living, eco-friendly solutions and environmentally responsible products.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Initiated in 1993, The Green Guide was published in the United States by the National Geographic Society. In cooperation with Environmental Defense Fund, the magazine began as a supplement to National Geographic and later gained a life of its own, being published on a quarterly basis.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Green Guide primarily focused on covering eco-friendly and sustainable products, green living solutions, and eco-travel. The content was written by experts in the field of environmental science and journalism.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazines also covered topics such as alternative transportation, energy-efficient appliances, natural personal care products, and gardening. It also analyzed food products based on their environmental impact, including nutritional value, health benefits, and environmental impact of food production.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence and Impact' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Green Guide was one of the earliest magazines to focus on environmentalism, with a special emphasis on practical applications of green living. The magazine achieved a significant readership by targeting mainstream households who wanted to live a greener life.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Closure' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Green Guide ceased publication in 2009, after a successful 16-year run. In a statement released by the National Geographic Society at the time, the magazine was described as no longer being economically viable due to the shift to digital consumption of content.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- GreenSource Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'GreenSource Magazine', N'greensource-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Trade publication focused on sustainable design and construction practices for architects and builders}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GreenSource magazine was a trade publication that targeted architects, builders, and designers who were interested in eco-friendly solutions for commercial and residential buildings. The magazine provided readers with information on sustainable design and construction practices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GreenSource magazine was first published in 2006 as a supplement to Building Design + Construction magazine, which was owned by McGraw-Hill Construction. In 2007, it became a standalone publication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine came into existence at a time when the construction industry was increasingly concerned with sustainable design practices. As environmental issues gained more prominence, builders and architects were looking for ways to design buildings that were more energy-efficient and environmentally friendly.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GreenSource magazine provided readers with in-depth articles on sustainable design and construction practices, such as energy efficiency, indoor air quality, sustainable materials, and water conservation in building projects. The magazine also featured case studies of green building projects, showcasing various sustainable design and construction practices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GreenSource magazine provided readers with expert analyses of green building products and technologies. The magazine also had regular sections on industry news, policy updates, and events related to sustainable design.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Awards and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GreenSource magazine was highly regarded within the construction industry and won numerous awards for its content. In 2008 and 2009, the magazine won the "Best Shelter Magazine" award at the Folio: Eddie & Ozzie Awards.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Closure' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2012, GreenSource magazine ceased publication. McGraw-Hill Construction stated that the magazine had fulfilled its mission of providing essential education and resources for sustainable building practices. Despite its closure, GreenSource magazine continued to be regarded as a highly influential publication within the construction industry, and its legacy remains today.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Grenadier Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Grenadier Magazine', N'the-grenadier-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Biannual publication covering history, traditions, and operations of Grenadier Guards regiment in British Army.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Grenadier magazine is a biannual publication for the Grenadier Guards regiment, one of the oldest regiments in the British Army. The magazine covers topics related to the history, traditions, and current operations of the regiment.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Grenadier magazine was first published in 1946, after the end of World War II, and has been published biannually ever since. The magazine is produced by the Grenadier Guards regimental association and includes articles written by serving and retired members of the regiment, as well as their families and friends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Grenadier magazine covers a range of topics related to the Grenadier Guards regiment, including its history, traditions, and role within the British Army. The magazine also features articles about current operations and deployments, as well as profiles of serving and retired members of the regiment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its regular content, The Grenadier magazine publishes obituaries of former members of the regiment, ensuring that their contributions are not forgotten.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Grenadier magazine is distributed to serving and retired members of the Grenadier Guards regiment, as well as their families and friends. It is also available to members of the public who are interested in the history and traditions of the regiment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Awards and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Grenadier magazine has received several awards over the years, including the prestigious Otto P. Zellman Award for best Military Periodical from the American Society of Journalists and Authors in 2000. The magazine also received the award for Best Military Journal from The Emerald Foundation in 2006.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Funding' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Grenadier magazine is funded through subscriptions, sales, and donations made by serving and retired members of the Grenadier Guards regiment and their families. The magazine is not affiliated with the British Army, but rather operates independently through the Grenadier Guards regimental association.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Grooves Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Grooves Magazine', N'grooves-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Global publication on electronic music culture, featuring interviews, reviews, and features on emerging artists and events.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grooves magazine is a magazine dedicated to electronic music. The magazine covers a range of genres and topics related to electronic music culture, including interviews, reviews, and features on notable artists and events.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grooves magazine was founded in 1998 by a group of electronic music enthusiasts in Germany. The magazine was originally titled "Groove - Das Magazin für elektronische Musik," which translates to "Groove - The Magazine for Electronic Music," and was published in German.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2006, Grooves magazine internationalized its content, translating articles into English and targeting a global audience. Since then, the magazine has been published in both German and English editions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grooves magazine covers a wide range of topics related to electronic music culture. The magazine includes interviews with artists, reviews of albums and live performances, and features on notable events and festivals.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is also known for its in-depth coverage of underground electronic music and emerging artists. Grooves magazine has contributed to the discovery and exposure of several artists who have become successful in the electronic music industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grooves magazine is distributed in several countries around the world, including Germany, the United States, and the UK. The magazine is available both in print and digital formats, with a website featuring exclusive content and articles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Awards and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grooves magazine has received several awards over the years, including the "Best Music Magazine" award at the German magazine awards in 2012. The magazine has been praised for its in-depth coverage of electronic music culture and its commitment to uncovering emerging artists.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Funding' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Grooves magazine is funded through advertising, subscriptions, and sales. The magazine is published by Groove Verlag GmbH, a media company based in Berlin, Germany.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Growing Without Schooling
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Growing Without Schooling', N'growing-without-schooling', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Magazine promoting unschooling, founded by John Holt, featuring practical advice, resources, essays and a community for homeschooling families.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Growing Without Schooling (GWS) was a magazine founded in 1977 by American educator and author, John Holt. The magazine focuses on unschooling, a type of homeschooling that prioritizes self-directed learning and allows children to explore their own interests without a structured curriculum.{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'John Holt, who had previously worked as a teacher and education reformer, founded GWS in response to what he perceived as failings in the traditional education system. Holt encouraged parents to trust their children''s natural desire to learn and to give them the freedom to follow their own path.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GWS was published from 1977 to 2001, producing 143 issues and reaching readers around the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GWS featured articles on unschooling, including practical advice and resources for parents who were interested in homeschooling their children. The magazine also included essays by Holt and other writers on the philosophy of unschooling and critiques of the traditional education system.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to print content, GWS provided a community for unschoolers to connect and share resources. The magazine sponsored conferences and events for homeschooling families and maintained a network of contributors and readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'GWS was highly influential in the unschooling and homeschooling movements, and played a key role in popularizing the concept of unschooling as a viable alternative to traditional education. Holt''s ideas about self-directed learning, child-centred education, and individuality have continued to influence educational reform movements around the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'After Holt''s death in 1985, GWS ceased publication but the magazine''s influence continued to be felt in the homeschooling and unschooling communities. Many former readers and contributors have gone on to become leaders in the movement, promoting Holt''s ideas and advocating for alternative education models.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, GWS is remembered as a key resource for unschooling families and a catalyst for educational reform. The magazine''s archives are available online, ensuring that its legacy continues to be accessible to current and future generations of readers.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Guantes Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Guantes Magazine', N'guantes-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A Latin American fashion and lifestyle magazine showcasing emerging designers and celebrating regional culture through content on trends, beauty, health, travel, and more.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guantes is a magazine based in Lima, Peru that focuses on fashion and lifestyle. The magazine covers topics including fashion trends, beauty, health, and travel, with an emphasis on Latin American culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guantes was founded in 2012 by a group of journalists and fashion experts in Lima. The magazine has since gained a following in Peru and throughout Latin America, featuring content in both Spanish and English.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guantes features articles on fashion and beauty trends, including celebrity interviews, runway reviews, and editorials. The magazine also covers lifestyle topics such as health and wellness, travel, and food.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guantes'' content reflects the diversity and vibrancy of Latin American culture, showcasing emerging designers, artists, and musicians from the region. The magazine also features collaborations with international brands and designers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guantes has established itself as a leading voice in the Latin American fashion and lifestyle community, promoting local talent and celebrating the region''s rich cultural heritage. The magazine has also helped to shift the conversation around fashion and beauty towards inclusivity and representation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Awards' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since its founding, Guantes has been recognized with several awards and accolades. In 2016, the magazine was named "Best Fashion and Lifestyle Magazine" at the Peruvian Journalism Awards. The following year, Guantes was honored with the "International Diversity Award" at the London Fashion Week.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Future' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'As Guantes continues to expand its reach, the magazine is expected to remain a key player in the Latin American fashion and lifestyle scene. With a focus on creativity, innovation, and inclusivity, Guantes is poised to shape the future of fashion media in the region.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Guitar for the Practicing Musician
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Guitar for the Practicing Musician', N'guitar-for-the-practicing-musician', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly music magazine for guitarists featuring interviews, lessons, gear reviews, and transcriptions of popular songs.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guitar for the Practicing Musician was a monthly music magazine published by Cherry Lane Music from 1983 to 1999. The magazine was aimed at guitarists and featured interviews, lessons, gear reviews, and transcriptions of popular songs.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guitar for the Practicing Musician was founded in 1983 by Howard Zimmerman, a former editor of Guitar Player magazine. It was initially published by Miller Freeman, Inc. before being sold to Cherry Lane Music in 1989.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine quickly gained a reputation for its high-quality content and commitment to guitar education. It was particularly popular among metal and hard rock guitarists, featuring exclusive interviews and lessons with top guitarists of the era, including Eddie Van Halen, Steve Vai, and Yngwie Malmsteen.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guitar for the Practicing Musician featured a wide range of content aimed at guitarists of all skill levels. The magazine included lessons on various playing styles and techniques, as well as gear reviews and recommendations.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition, Guitar for the Practicing Musician regularly featured interviews with prominent guitarists, in which they discussed their playing styles, inspirations, and techniques. The magazine also included transcriptions of popular songs, allowing readers to learn to play them for themselves.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Guitar for the Practicing Musician was widely regarded as one of the best guitar magazines of its era, thanks to its in-depth content and commitment to guitar education. The magazine''s lessons and transcriptions helped countless guitarists to improve their playing and learn new techniques.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition, Guitar for the Practicing Musician played an important role in shaping the guitar industry, helping to popularize certain styles of playing and introduce guitarists to new gear and technology.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although Guitar for the Practicing Musician ceased publication in 1999, its impact on the guitar world lives on. The magazine influenced several generations of guitarists and helped to shape the sound of 80s and 90s rock and metal.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition, many of the magazine''s lessons and transcriptions have been compiled into books and DVDs, ensuring that its content remains widely available to guitarists around the world. Today, Guitar for the Practicing Musician is remembered as one of the most influential and beloved guitar magazines of all time.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gulfscapes Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Gulfscapes Magazine', N'gulfscapes-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A lifestyle magazine showcasing the beauty and culture of the Gulf Coast of Texas, with content focused on outdoor activities, dining, travel, and regional history.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gulfscapes is a regional lifestyle magazine based in Corpus Christi, Texas. The magazine features content on southern Texas'' culture, outdoor activities, dining, and travel.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gulfscapes was launched in 1994 by a local team led by founder and publisher, Bill Clough. The magazine''s mission was to showcase the beauty and culture of the Gulf Coast of Texas, as well as promote education and conservation of the region.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Gulfscapes has developed a reputation for high-quality content that highlights the best the Gulf Coast has to offer.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gulfscapes content is focused on a wide variety of topics covering everything from coastal lifestyles, outdoor activities, events, showcase of Gulf Coast businesses, and conservation efforts. The magazine regularly features interviews with local personalities and business owners, as well as stories about regional history and culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s photography and layout are of high quality, showcasing the beauty of the Texas Gulf Coast. The magazine has won numerous recognitions for its photography, layout, and writing.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gulfscapes is distributed quarterly and is available in several outlets like hotel lobbies, local restaurants, museums, and other businesses. Also, the magazine can be found in bookstores and on the Gulfscapes website. A digital version of the magazine is also available for purchase.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gulfscapes has been an influential publication in the Gulf Coast region, promoting regional culture, tourism, and conservation. The magazine''s coverage has been acknowledged and endorsed by various bodies and organizations in the region.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition, the magazine has been the recipient of numerous editorial and design awards and nominations. Gulfscapes has helped promote Southern Texas'' culture to readers worldwide.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, Gulfscapes remains a well-respected magazine, showcasing the beauty, history, ecology, and entertainment of the southern Gulf Coast of Texas. The magazine has remained visually strong. It enjoys a loyal reader base as the magazine continues to highlight the beauty of the Gulf coast region.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gunton's Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Gunton''s Magazine', N'guntons-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A Victorian-era publication focusing on outdoor pursuits, conservation, and rural life in England, known for high-quality illustrations.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gunton''s Magazine was a periodical publication produced in England from 1857 to 1893. The magazine was influential in publishing articles and illustrations about hunting, fishing, natural history, and country life.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Founded in 1857 by John Edward Harting, Gunton''s Magazine focused on the interests of the country gentleman with an emphasis on outdoor pursuits.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Initially, the magazine''s content covered fishing and hunting, but as it expanded, it included more articles on natural history, travels and adventures, and rural customs.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gunton''s Magazine was published for 37 years, and during this time, it established itself as a leading publication in its field. It was considered to be the finest sporting magazine in England during its time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gunton''s Magazine features a wide range of articles and illustrations, including information about hunting, shooting, fishing, and other outdoor activities. The magazine also included articles on natural history, countryside topics, and travel.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s illustrations were of high quality, depicting animals, landscapes, and equipment used in outdoor pursuits. Many of the illustrations were from notable artists, such as Sir Edwin Landseer, Joseph Wolf, and John Leech.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gunton''s Magazine was influential in promoting outdoor pursuits, promoting conservation of the countryside, and documenting rural life in England. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine contributed to the development of the conservation movement in Britain by disseminating information about species protection, habitat conservation, and the need for sustainable practices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although Gunton''s Magazine ceased publication in 1893, it remains an important historical document, providing an insight into the sporting and cultural history of England during the Victorian period.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since its publication, the magazine has been prized by collectors and enthusiasts for its vivid illustrations and informative articles, and it is still relevant for those who have an interest in the outdoors or for those interested in the cultural and social history of rural lifestyle.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- Harting, J. E. (2010). Gunton''s Magazine. Cambridge University Press. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "Gunton''s Magazine," The New Encyclopedia Britannica, Vol. 14, 2001, pp. 158-159.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

