VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine providing practical advice and tutorials for building and repairing electronic devices, as well as news and opinions related to the electronics industry.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics was a monthly magazine dedicated to the practical aspects of electronics. The magazine provided readers with tips and tutorials for building and repairing electronic devices, as well as news and opinions related to the electronics industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics was first published in 1983 by Gernsback Publications. The magazine was aimed at electronics enthusiasts and professionals, providing practical advice for building and repairing electronic devices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Hands-On Electronics published articles on a wide range of topics, including audio amplifiers, digital circuits, microcontrollers, and more. The magazine also featured detailed construction projects, complete with circuit diagrams and parts lists.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its focus on practical electronics, the magazine also included news and opinion pieces related to the electronics industry, as well as interviews with prominent figures in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics'' content was divided into several sections, including features, projects, news, and opinion pieces. The magazine also included a regular column titled "Electronics Q&A," which provided readers with answers to common questions about electronic devices and circuits.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s construction projects were a major focus, often featuring detailed instructions and diagrams for building everything from simple gadgets to complex audio systems. The magazine also included equipment reviews, helping readers to make informed decisions about purchasing electronic equipment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics played an important role in the growth and development of the electronics industry, providing readers with practical advice and tutorials for building and repairing electronic devices. The magazine helped to build a sense of community among electronics enthusiasts, and provided a platform for sharing knowledge and ideas.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although the magazine is no longer in publication, its legacy lives on through the many practical projects and tutorials that it published over the years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- Vagnoni, Anthony. "Hands-On Electronics Magazine: An Overview." Electronic Design, 24 Oct. 1994, www.electronicdesign.com/technologies/test-measurement/article/21774467/handson-electronics-magazine-an-overview.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "Hands-On Electronics Magazine." WorldCat, www.worldcat.org/title/hands-on-electronics-magazine/oclc/18337606.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Hardgainer Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Hardgainer Magazine', N'hardgainer-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A Bi-Monthly magazine providing practical advice on strength training and bodybuilding for individuals who struggle to gain muscle mass.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction{{Image image:magazine-cover-not-available.png|Type=PrimaryArticleImage}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer was a bi-monthly magazine focused on strength training and bodybuilding for individuals naturally prone to difficulty in gaining muscle mass, called "hardgainers". The magazine was known for its practical advice and emphasis on progressive overload training principles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer was founded in 1989 by Stuart McRobert, an author and bodybuilder who wrote extensively on the subject of strength training. The magazine quickly gained a following among individuals who struggled to gain muscle mass, offering practical advice for building strength and size.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Hardgainer published articles on a wide range of topics related to strength training and bodybuilding, including training routines, nutrition, and supplementation. The magazine also emphasized the importance of progress tracking and the use of free weights in workouts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer''s content was divided into several sections, including training, nutrition, and supplementation. The magazine''s training section included workout routines and tips for building strength and muscle mass.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The nutrition section focused on providing practical advice for individuals with fast metabolisms or digestive issues, ensuring that they were able to consume enough nutrients to support muscle growth. The magazine also provided supplement recommendations, but emphasized that supplements are not a substitute for proper nutrition.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the magazine''s recurring features was the "Hardgainer Q&A," which answered reader-submitted questions related to training, nutrition, and supplementation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer played an important role in the bodybuilding and fitness industry, providing practical advice for individuals who had difficulty gaining muscle mass. The magazine emphasized the importance of progressive overload training principles and tracking progress, two concepts that are still highly regarded in the fitness community today.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although the magazine is no longer in publication, its legacy lives on through the many practical training tips and principles that it espoused over the years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- McRobert, Stuart. "Hardgainer magazine: the story, philosophy and practical wisdom of the original Hardgainer." Haverford, PA: CS Publishing Ltd., 2019.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "Hardgainer Magazine." WorldCat, www.worldcat.org/title/hardgainer-magazine/oclc/25944533.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

